('', ' Musee d\'Orsay skip-the-line', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.908174585065!2d2.324367350855784!3d48.8599613791859!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e2bb630941b%3A0xd071bd8cb14423d8!2sMus%C3%A9e+d&#39;Orsay!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501602346627" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 230, 2, 'Visites', 'Although the visit to the Musee dâ€™Orsay focuses on the paintings of the Impressionists, we will cover a large range of artistic styles and movements of the XIX century. This tour will allow you to understand the origins of Impressionism, its development, and the reasons why it was rejected by most of French society and by art critics at the time. As well as simply admiring their lively, luminous paintings, you will also be encouraged to note the individual style of each Impressionist, and will learn about their lives in order to better understand their works.', 'Tous les jours', ' Musee d\'Orsay skip-the-line'),
('', ' The Marie-Anoinette\'s tour', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d10499.76778223949!2d2.3511232774002653!3d48.85931741697251!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e03cdce4ae9%3A0x38cfa580446f9e46!2sLe+Marais%2C+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501601504826" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 180, 3, 'Visites', 'Private sightseeing tour Introduction:\r\nGuided tour in Le Marais, Paris\r\n<br>\r\nLet\'s stroll in le Marais, this area of Paris which is full of splendid private mansions that plunge us into the time of Marie-Antoinette, this special atmosphere of the XVIIIth century, its sophistication, its pleasure and its violence...\r\n<br>\r\nThis tour last 3 hours, and include a chocolate and a macaron tasting.\r\n<br>\r\nYour guide has a master degree in History in La Sorbonne, and is specialised of the XVIIIth century.\r\n<br>\r\nTour Duration: 3 Hours\r\nMaximum Number of People: 6\r\nTour Type: Walking Only\r\nTour Price: Price Per Group EUR â‚¬180,00\r\nTour Highlights:\r\nThis tour is about the refined pleasure of the XVIIIth century: aesthetic and culinary. It will be a lovely stroll in the maze of streets of Le Marais.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Marais is full of beautiful private mansions of the XVII and XVIIIth century. I will show you some magnificient decors, some very refined furniture and some luxury items that could have been those of Marie Antoinette. I will show you what kind of cultural context this period has produced.\r\n<br>\r\nAdded to this aesthetic walk, this will be a gustative stroll. You will discover the best chocolate maker of Paris, where the parisian palaces buy their chocolate from. During Marie-Antoinette\'s time, the chocolate was a privilege of the royal court.\r\n<br>\r\nWe will end the tour with a macaron tasting produced by the same house of gastronomy than the one that used to supply the royal court of Versailles.\r\n<br>\r\nThis will be an unforgettable trip in the refined culture of the Ancien Regime that still exists in Paris. This walk is in a very swinging and elegant district, full of lovely shops, and art galleries. . . We might stop there too!!\r\n<br>\r\nTour Inclusions:\r\nThe private guide and the entrance fees to the private mansions are included too.\r\n<br>\r\nTour Exclusions:\r\nThe chocolate and macaroon tasting are extra.', 'Tous les jours', ' The Marie-Anoinette\'s tour'),
('', '4 departementsÂ  with their own landscapes', 'Normandis/ Bretagne', '', 70, 8, 'Visites', 'Walking tour in the village 2h\r\nShort visit to the abbey 1h\r\nLong visit to the abbey 2h\r\nVisit to the abbey + the village 3h\r\n\r\n4 departementsÂ  with their own landscapes and personnalities :\r\nFinistÃ¨re : the Far West of France, where celtic traditions are still so prevalent.\r\nMorbihan : the South, with its mild weather and the famous Golfe du Morbihan.\r\nCÃ´tes d\'Armor : 347 kms of coastline and 3 natural reserves and the Pink Granit Coast.\r\nIlle-et-Vilaine : on the Breton Marchlands, a variety of cities and landscapes and the capital : Rennes.\r\n', 'Tous les jours', '4 departementsÂ  with their own landscapes'),
('', 'A taste of Italy: La Dolce Vita in the Italian villages', 'French-Riviera', '', 225, 7, 'Visites', '150 years ago, the county of Nice was part of the kingdom of Piedmont and Sardinia, its capital was Torino and not Paris and its inhabitants spoke NiÃ§ois and Italian and not French.\r\nIn 1860, history wrote a new chapter, Nice became French and at 20 km, a border separated 2 countries: France and Italy.\r\nAcross this border you will find a completely different world with many medieval villages, charming people, excellent food and a delicious Cappuccino.\r\nAs an expert from Italy, let me explain the different ways of living between Italy and France, cultural differences and different economic aspects while visiting wonderful villages, meeting locals and Enjoy a delicious Italian meal.\r\nChange country for the time of a tour that will take you to my favorite places across the border.', 'Tous les jours', 'A taste of Italy: La Dolce Vita in the Italian villages'),
