('', 'Biarritz', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d46328.04530844639!2d-1.590897912265711!3d43.47097568034126!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd51152b0af31e33%3A0x40665174813a830!2s64200+Biarritz!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501767667049" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', '', '', 'Biarritz'),
('', 'Biarritz Walking Historical Tour', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2894.7446208910633!2d-1.5583932850929951!3d43.4867996711939!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd516ad965f33079%3A0xd63e14756c3daaa!2sH%C3%B4tel+du+Palais!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499850438774" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 35, 2, 'Sightseeing-Tour', '\r\n\r\nCome walk the famous Biarritz Grande Plage, La Rocher de la Vierge and La CÃ´te des Basques with us and discover Biarritzâ€™s rich history, beautiful coast line and eclectic architecture.\r\n<br>\r\nForever branded by the passage of Napoleon III and the famous Eugenie, Biarritz has always been one of Franceâ€™s most welcoming towns. Get an insight into the different lives experienced in Biarritz, from the humble life of the whalers to the extravagant lives of the wealthy aristocrats. Take the opportunity to go inside the ornate hotel du Palais, built in 1855, stroll along the grande plage and see the waves that surfers come from all over the world to surf.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\nPassionate and experienced local guide (French and English speaking)\r\nSmall intimate groups\r\nMeeting point : HÃ´tel du Palais, 1 Avenue de lâ€™ImpÃ©ratrice\r\nDuration : 1.5 hours\r\n ', 'monday, wednesday,friday,sunday', 'BIARRITZ WALKING HISTORICAL TOUR'),
('', 'Bike tour + museum', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499850612073" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 120, 4, 'Bike', 'Combined Guided Tour Bicycle + Museum\r\nThese combined tours let you learn and have fun at the same time\r\n<br>\r\nAll of this with â€œpreferred accessâ€: no waiting in line.\r\n<br>\r\nCombine fun and culture. Explore and discover a part of Paris before experiencing the most captivating Parisian museum of your choice.\r\nOur fully-accredited National Guides put you at the front of the line and allow you to get the most out of your visit. Their expertise will guide you to a selection of the finest works of art representing a wide range of genres.\r\n<br>\r\nCombined Guided Tour : Bicycle + Louvre Museum\r\nNot only do you explore the historical heart of Paris, your National Guide reveals all its secrets. From bourgeoisie and royal scandals to the hardships of daily life and revolutions. And youâ€™ll find out why Paris was named Paris; the historic link between the city and the Centre Pompidou; and the Palais Royal, the geographic centre of the capital, the home of the oldest commercial centre in Europe.\r\nYour stop at the Louvre museum goes beyond words as you experience the most breathtaking masterpieces from Venus de Milo to the French Crown Jewels, and the incomparable Mona Lisa.\r\n<br>\r\nIncluded:\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nProfessional National Guide\r\nInsurance\r\nBooking the museum or monument\r\nTickets to museums and/or monuments (skip the line â€“ no waiting)\r\n\r\n', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'bike tour + museum'),
('', 'Bike tour + Tasting', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499850924994" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 79, 4, 'Bike', 'Private tour Bike Tour + tasting\r\nDiscover the Paris that only a Parisian could know.  From the Place de la Bastille to the Quais de Seine along with the most Parisian market and enjoy all the high-quality produce of the region: croissants, dried sausage, cheese, gratin dauphinois and coffee.\r\n<br>\r\nAfter this taste adventure, become a virtual Parisian and head for the places where the locals get together; youâ€™ll better get to know, thanks to Paris Bike Tourâ€™s professional guide, the multiple layers of the City of Light. Compare the architecture of the City Hall of Paris with the modern BibliothÃ¨que (library) Nationale FranÃ§ois Mitterrand while learning what the life of a Parisian is really like within the busiest parts of the city. Other places to go will be suggested so that throughout your visit you can better live the life of a Parisian.\r\n<br>\r\nSights and stops\r\nCentre Pompidou\r\nLe Marais / rue de Franc Bourgeois\r\nPlace de Vosges\r\nPlace de la Bastille / OpÃ©ra\r\nLe Faubourg Saint-Antoine\r\nFood tasting at a covered market: CafÃ©, croissant, an assortment of cheeses and deli meats and a "surprise of the day"\r\nParc de Bercy\r\nPasserelle Simon de Beauvoir\r\nBibliothÃ¨que nationale de France (BnF)\r\nQuais de Seine / Square Tino Rossi\r\nInstitut du Monde Arabe\r\nNotre Dame?-Place de lâ€™HÃ´tel de Ville\r\n<br>\r\nThe price include\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket, rain-poncho\r\nProfessional National Guide\r\nFood tasting at the market\r\nInsurance\r\nExtras during the food tasting.\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in French, English and German', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'Bike tour + Tasting'),
