('', 'City tour the best of Paris full day', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d83998.94740156252!2d2.2773451864780037!3d48.858837635028124!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1f06e2b70f%3A0x40b82c3688c9460!2sParis!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501601708980" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 440, 8, 'Visites', 'Join me on my guided tour and discover the best of Paris in just one day. During the tour you will see Notre-Dame, the Louvre, the Champs-Elysees, the Arc de Triomphe, the Invalides, the Latin Quarter, Place de la Concorde, Place de lâ€™Opera, Place Vendome. You will learn the history of Paris and each of its monuments and appreciate their beauty all the more. Besides the aforementioned attractions, you can also visit Montmartre, Saint-Germain-des-Pres or discover art in one of Parisâ€™ museums such as the Louvre or the Musee dâ€™Orsay.\r\n\r\nThis tour can be organized to fit your needs, so your suggestions are welcome. To get from one sight to another, we can use public transport, a taxi or even a cruise boat, which goes from the Eiffel Tower to Notre-Dame and stops at all major landmarks.', 'Tous les jours', 'City tour: the best of Paris (full day)'),
('', 'City tour the best of Paris half day', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d83998.94740156252!2d2.2773451864780037!3d48.858837635028124!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1f06e2b70f%3A0x40b82c3688c9460!2sParis!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501601708980" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 285, 4, 'Visites', 'Join me on my guided tour and discover the best of Paris. On a half-day tour, you will see Notre-Dame, the Louvre, the Champs-Elysees, the Arc de Triomphe, the Invalides, the Latin Quarter, Place de la Concorde, Place de lâ€™Opera, Place Vendome. You will learn the history of Paris and each of its monuments and appreciate their beauty all the more.\r\n\r\nThis tour can be organized to fit your needs, so your suggestions are welcome. To get from one sight to another, we can use public transport, a taxi or even a cruise boat, which goes from the Eiffel Tower to Notre-Dame and stops at all major landmarks.', 'Tous les jours', 'City tour: the best of Paris (half day)'),
('', 'Classic Gourmet Tour', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 330, 3, 'Visites', 'This tour focuses on tasting the sumptuous flavors of Bordeaux with scenic and historical walks linking our tastings. We will have the opportunity to visit one of the most famous and old cheese dairy in Bordeaux, as well as its vaulted cellars for the preservation of cheese, dating from the 15th century. Here we will find a treasure of cheeses that slowly takes on age. Here, a treasure of cheeses is offered to us, slowly taking age during their maturity period, this aging process being explained by one of their expert employee. We will taste three cheeses and enjoy the atmosphere of the old underground cellars.\r\nThen, we visit a Bordeaux society known worldwide for the rebirth of the canelÃ©s, typically regional dessert, originally prepared by the nuns for school children. We will learn the history of this traditional dessert and why its creation in Bordeaux has a link with wine! We will relax by enjoying this sweetness accompanied by a hot drink.\r\nTo finish, we will end with the joy of a wine tasting. A small wine bar will welcome us in its sunny courtyard where we taste three Bordeaux wines. Each one has its unique style, selected and presented for us, by its sommelier.', 'Tous les jours', 'Classic Gourmet Tour'),
