('', 'For children', 'Strasbourg', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d168968.42259219624!2d7.6216654371894315!3d48.56902817129283!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4796c8495e18b2c1%3A0x971a483118e7241f!2sStrasbourg!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501773022940" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'A visit adapted to younger visitors who will think about the Strasbourg of the past.\r\nEducational collaboration with teachers for school groups.', '', 'For children'),
('', 'France, Italy and Monaco (3 Countries in 1 Day)', 'French-Riviera', '', 225, 7, 'Visites', 'This tour takes advantage of our very particular geographical position which places 3 countries in a distance of only 10 km.\r\nWe start the day with a panoramic walk on the marvelous coastal roads, breathtaking photos and a visit to the medieval mountain village of Eze or, if you prefer the beautiful city of Menton.\r\nWe then pass the border and visit one of the many charming Italian villages. You will get a bit of Italian flavor and you will discover the differences and similarities of these two neighboring countries. After a typical lunch in a local restaurant, we cross two borders and visit one of the smallest countries in the world: the Principality of Monaco.\r\nWe will take a panoramic walk through the city, partly on the famous Formula 1 race track that leads directly through the city center. We will make a stop on the legendary Place du Casino and visit the old town where you can see the palace, the cathedral and from where you can enjoy magnificent views.', 'Tous les jours', 'France, Italy and Monaco (3 Countries in 1 Day)'),
('', 'French and Alsacian Wine Tasting', 'Strasbourg', '', 28, 2, 'French-Gastronomy', 'We organize Alsatian & French Wine tastings in Strasbourg. Through our network of partners (wine shops / wine bars / wine-tasting cellars), we can fulfil all requests:\r\n<br>\r\nIntroduction Alsace wines\r\nDiscovery of Alsatian wines\r\nWine & food pairing\r\nOenology lessons\r\nWine Tasting evenings\r\nWe invite you to contact us in order to explain your request and ask for a free quote.\r\n<br>\r\nWine Tasting Example\r\nFor a tasting at 28 â‚¬ TTC / person you can enjoy:\r\n\r\n3 glasses of wine\r\n1 cheese & charcuterie platter to share', 'Everyday', 'French and Alsacian Wine Tasting');
