('', 'Golf Lessons in Biarritz', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d5791.968624786254!2d-1.5797458752626665!3d43.460924703988795!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5114c12ea6a87b%3A0x9435bbe3b9e5786f!2sCentre+International+d&#39;entra%C3%AEnement+au+golf+d&#39;Ilbarritz!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499854122547" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 45, 2, 'Golf', '\r\nGolf lessons\r\n<br>\r\nBiarritz golf courses have forever been a gathering place for the best European players and, in its past, the golfing playground for Kings and the wealthy aristocracy. Perched on the cliff tops of the famous Basque Coast is the 9 hole IlBiarritz golf course. This golf course has been specifically designed as a training ground and ensures that all practical game situations can be experienced. Biarritz by Locals offers golf lessons to cater to all levels whether you are trying golf for the first time or are wanting to improve your short or long game.\r\n<br>\r\nCome and improve the way you play and take in the breathtaking views of the sparkling Basque coast line at the same time.\r\n<br>\r\nThe package\r\n<br>\r\nProfessional instructor (French and English speaking)\r\nEquipment\r\nMeeting point: Golf dâ€™Illbarritz\r\nDuration: 1.5 hours', 'Everyday on demand', 'GOLF LESSONS IN BIARRITZ'),
('', 'Gourmand Strasbourg', 'Strasbourg', '', 90, 4, 'French-Gastronomy', 'The Historic Island of Strasbourg, listed as World Heritage by UNESCO, is home to many local merchants who honour the Alsatian terroir.\r\n<br>\r\nIt is no coincidence that the locals always shop in the small local shops of the old town. At the heart of this neighborhood you will find the authentic atmosphere of Alsatian culture.\r\n<br>\r\nDuring our 4 hour tour immerse yourself in this unique place and live â€œStrasbourg Gourmandâ€ by meeting its people.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Highlights\r\nFor this visit, we have selected for you 10 typical tastings that will take place in 7 local shops where the owners will warmly open their doors to allow you to discover their products.\r\n<br>\r\nThroughout this visit, your guide will be happy to share his knowledge about the history and culture of his city while letting you discover the best sights of the old city.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Tastings\r\nDare to taste the Flammekueche (litteraly â€œflame pieâ€) in the typical way â€“ with your hands! It will be served alongside one of the classics of the Alsatian vineyard: a glass of Riesling\r\nTry to tame the charismatic local farmhouse cheese, Munster, produced in our green valleys\r\nYou canâ€™t visit Alsace without biting into an Alsatian Pretzel straight from the bakerâ€™s oven\r\nTake the time to sit down around a generous and tasty sauerkraut which is eaten traditionally accompanied by a glass of beer brewed near Strasbourg\r\nTry to guess the subtle blends of spices that make up the famous Alsatian gingerbread\r\nChocolates mades with regional flavors by a famous chocolatier will round off your gourmand trip through Strasbourg.\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWe speak French, German and English\r\nDo not hesitate to contact us for tours in other languages ??like Italien, Spanish and Japanese.\r\n<br>\r\nQualifications\r\nAll the guides we work with are cardholders of â€ Official Tour Guide â€ which ensures a high level of qualification and visits supervised by professionals.', 'Every day', 'Gourmand Strasbourg'),
('', 'Gourmet Deluxe Tour', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 410, 4, 'Visites', 'This tour focuses on tasting the sumptuous flavors of Bordeaux with scenic and historical walks linking our tastings. We will have the opportunity to visit one of the most famous and old cheese dairy in Bordeaux, as well as its vaulted cellars for the preservation of cheese, dating from the 15th century. Here we will find a treasure of cheeses that slowly takes on age. Here, a treasure of cheeses is offered to us, slowly taking age during their maturity period, this aging process being explained by one of their expert employee. We will taste three cheeses and enjoy the atmosphere of the old underground cellars.\\r\\nThen, we visit a Bordeaux society known worldwide for the rebirth of the canelÃ©s, typically regional dessert, originally prepared by the nuns for school children. We will learn the history of this traditional dessert and why its creation in Bordeaux has a link with wine! We will relax by enjoying this sweetness accompanied by a hot drink.\\r\\nTo finish, we will end with the joy of a wine tasting. A small wine bar will welcome us in its sunny courtyard where we taste three Bordeaux wines. Each one has its unique style, selected and presented for us, by its sommelier.', 'Tous les jours', 'Gourmet Deluxe Tour'),
('', 'Gourmet Strasbourg', 'Strasbourg', '', 135, 4, 'French-Gastronomy', 'Discover Strasbourg through iconic specialties refined to satisfy gourmetsâ€™ palates. You will visit Strasbourgâ€™s renowned shops and discover the best local products paired with Alsatian fine wines.\r\n<br>\r\nSelecting the tour â€œStrasbourg Gourmetâ€ is also a good idea for people who want to experiment the Alsatian way of life, follow your guide and take a seat in a local â€œWinstubâ€ (eatery) to taste a traditional meal: the Baeckeoffe.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Highlights\r\nDuring the 4.5 hour tour devoted to the finest dishes of the Alsatian gastronomic culture, you will take part in 8 tastings in selected places.\r\n<br>\r\nThroughout this visit, your guide will be happy to share their knowledge about the history and culture of his city while letting you discover the best sights of the old city.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Tastings\r\nGo to the Westermann Bakery, starred chef family, whose reputation is second to none! Try a staple of Alsatian gastronomy: some of the best Kougelhopf in the region. Then your guide will select some of the finest breads to accompany the next tasting.\r\nA selection of Alsatian charcuterie & foie gras will be presented by our local butcher\r\nThen, you will visit a typical French fromagerie to find exceptional cheeses including a PDO Munster made in the purest tradition.\r\nMeet our sommelier around Krutenau neightborood, off the beaten track. He will be happy to let you discover Alsatian wines with the products collected along our tour.\r\nThen, in an authentic â€œWinstubâ€ you will have the opportunity to acquaint yourself with the Alsatian â€œBaeckeoffeâ€, less well-known than sauerkraut but famous among connaisseurs\r\nThe tour will conclude in the tea house of the prestigious Christian lounge where you can choose from a selection of French pastries accompanied by coffee and chocolates made by renowned pastry maker and chocolatier Christopher Meyer.', 'Everyday', 'Gou