('', 'Les Alpages des Aravis et ses villages fleuris', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d708948.3202509595!2d5.863210308888751!3d46.044528060055356!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x478c09f4796a177d%3A0x308ab2ae4b92a20!2sHaute-Savoie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501844702883" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'The Aravis:\r\nTake the time to dawdle at the foot of the wild Aravis mountains, in beautiful Alpine villages such as the Grand Bornand or Clusaz. Discover the Chartreuse du Reposoir at the bottom of its valley.\r\nMeet in a mountain cottage a farmer willing to reveal the manufacture of the reblochon, ancestral formation, and to learn with him the life of a peasant in the 21st century. Stop at Morette Museum to understand the dramatic moments of resistance during the last war.\r\nAnd go to the church of ThÃ´nes, to admire one of the most beautiful baroque altarpieces of Haute Savoie.', '', 'Les Alpages des Aravis et ses villages fleuris'),
('', 'Lido', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.2605282472878!2d2.2987262151177243!3d48.87230980768147!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66fe9ffe3067f%3A0xefdcb0a11d9c593b!2s116+Av.+des+Champs-%C3%89lys%C3%A9es%2C+75008+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499854809226" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 170, 3, 'Show', '\r\n\r\nA private driver and his convertible citroen 2CV in front of your hotel...it\'s only the begining of your nightâ€¦ and already the parisian monuments are yours for an uncredible one hour rideâ€¦Champs-ElysÃ©es, Tour Eiffel, Notre Dame, Louvreâ€¦\r\n<br>\r\nProlong this exceptional evening at the Lido...Delight in the Revue "Bonheur" with 70 artists on stage including the famous Bluebell Girls and the Lido Boy Dancers. See breathtaking scenes, a real ice rink, 23 sets and 600 sumptuous costumes.... The Lido is more spectacular than ever!\r\n<br>\r\n1/2 bottle of champagne per person!\r\n<br>\r\nChoose between our different options :\r\n\r\n2CV tour (1h) + Dinner + Revue (2h30)\r\n\r\nDeparture 2CV: 18h \r\nMenu Plaisir :(the menu)\r\n170â‚¬/pers (3 pers/car)\r\n180â‚¬/pers (2 pers/car)\r\n2CV tour (1h) + Revue (1h30)\r\nDeparture 2CV: 20h or 21h30\r\n130 â‚¬/pers (3 pers/car)\r\n140 â‚¬/pers (2 pers/car)\r\n<br>\r\nRETURN NOT INCLUDED AFTER THE SHOW\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'every day', 'Lido'),
('', 'Local east parisian tour', 'Paris', '', 179, 2, 'Sightseeing-tour', 'This tour is made for those who already know a bit about Paris but want to visit the more local areas where you can see wonderful places, very romantic architecture and streets rather than touristy landmarks. The East is one of the most stunning part of Paris. We begin with the bottom of the hill of Montmartre, rue des abbesses which is a nice maze of tiny streets. \r\n<br>\r\nItinerary of the tour*\r\n\r\nFrom there we head to the east and cross the canal Saint Martin and we see Saint Serge Church, Parc des Buttes Chaumont, MouzaÃ¯a district, private houses and adorable and calm neighborhood in which you can admire very old â€œRegardâ€ and other 18th century buildings. Telegraphe wich is the truly highest point of Paris and we admire the wonderful view from rue Piat, above les jardins de Belleville. Proceeding down to Pere Lachaise through Menilmontand, Bastille and Le Marais. * The itinerary may vary depending on traffic or your desires.\r\n<br>\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'Every Day', 'Local east parisian tour'),
('', 'Local market tour and tasting', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2895.0980810028605!2d-1.5662599850932553!3d43.4794234716694!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd516b2931365b89%3A0xcfbac3f4bc7976ca!2s47+Rue+Gambetta%2C+64200+Biarritz!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499855574568" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 55, 2, 'Sightseeing-Tour ', '\r\nLocal market tour and tasting\r\n<br>\r\nJoin us on our favourite local market tour and tasting of the colourful Les Halles de Biarritz!\r\n<br>\r\nWhilst walking around the stalls, enjoy the lively and vibrant atmosphere this local market has to offer. Meet the producers and vendors, learn about the culinary traditions and local history and discover some of the finest products the Basque Country has to offer. Youâ€™ll taste your way from stall to stall enjoying delicious locally produced foie gras, fresh oysters and seafood, specialty cured meats, cheese, wine, coffee and the famous â€˜GÃ¢teau Basqueâ€™.\r\n<br>\r\nAfter this local market tour you will know all the hotspots of Les Halles that you will surely want to return again during your stayâ€¦\r\n<br>\r\nThe package\r\n<br>\r\nPassionate and experienced local guide (French and English speaking)\r\nMultiple tastings of regional products: oysters and sea food, â€œfoie grasâ€, cured ham, cheese, wine and basque cake.\r\nGroup sizes vary between 2 to 8 guests\r\nMeeting point : In front of the HÃ´tel Silhouette, 30 rue Gambetta, 64200 Biarritz\r\nDuration : 1.5 hours', 'Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday', 'LOCAL MARKET TOUR AND TASTING'),
('', 'Louvre & Musee dâ€™Orsay', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.90817458507!2d2.3243673508557894!3d48.85996137918592!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e2bb630941b%3A0xd071bd8cb14423d8!2sMus%C3%A9e+d&#39;Orsay!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501601933069" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 320, 5, 'Visites', 'If you come to Paris for a few days and want to make the most of your time, this tour is perfect for you. In just a few hours, you will be able to admire the worldâ€™s most famous sculptures and paintings including works by Leonardo da Vinci, Raphael, Michelangelo, Claude Monet, Edgar Degas, Van Gogh. Starting with classical art in the Louvre, we will follow the chronological development of artistic movements and continue on with the Impressionists at the Musee dâ€™Orsay (the two museums are located within a 10 to 15 minute walk from each other). Even if you are not an art-lover, you may be surprised at how fascinating it can be to learn about art when you find yourself standing in front of some of the best examples.', 'Tous les jours', ' Combo tour: Louvre & Musee dâ€™Orsay'),
('', 'Louvre skip-the-line', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.874102370468!2d2.335449950855805!3d48.8606110791861!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e671d877937b0f%3A0xb975fcfa192f84d4!2sMus%C3%A9e+du+Louvre!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501602014743" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 230, 2, 'Visites', 'As the Louvre is among the top-3 â€œvisits to be madeâ€ in Paris, the Louvre has its own 3 â€œthings to seeâ€: the Venus of Milo, the Winged Victory of Samothrace and, of course, the Mona Lisa. However, our visit will include much more than these â€œThree ladies of the Louvreâ€. In fact, during our comparatively short visit, I will try to construct a kind of art history timeline for you going from the Greco-Roman era to the very beginning of the19th century, pointing out the most important and most representative artistic examples of each period. I will also explain why such works are considered to be masterpieces and how they have contributed to the artistic heritage of the world.\r\n\r\n', 'Tous les jours', 'Louvre skip-the-line'),
('', 'Louvres-Tuileries', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d5249.5964065029075!2d2.3281810466812973!3d48.86205832498313!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e671d877937b0f%3A0xb975fcfa192f84d4!2sMus%C3%A9e+du+Louvre!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501583160268" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 200, 2, 'Visites', '', 'Tous les jours', 'Louvres-Tuileries'),
('', 'Macarons', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.7810262763!2d-0.6563530792514479!3d44.86370644020657!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501767704527" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', '', '', 'Macarons'),
('', 'Marais Tour', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d10499.76778223949!2d2.3511232774002653!3d48.85931741697251!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e03cdce4ae9%3A0x38cfa580446f9e46!2sLe+Marais%2C+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501601370212" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 250, 3, 'Visites', 'Private sightseeing tour Introduction:\r\nPrivate tour in the historical center of Paris, the aristocratic area of the Marais. On foot or by bicycle.\r\n<br>\r\nToday, the Marais is a trendy area, with bohemian and effortless elegance. Located in the center of Paris, Parisians love to stroll around this unique area due to it\'s rich historical past. Art galleries, boutiques with avant-garde fashion, designers, lively cafÃ©s, market... The vitality of the Marais attracts lovers of history and a creativ and artistic crowd.\r\n<br>\r\nYour guide is a local, who was raised there since it\'s birth. Therefore, she knows the charming places and theirs secrets...\r\n\r\nTour Duration: 3 Hours\r\nMaximum Number of People: 6\r\nTour Type: Walking Only\r\nTour Price: Price Per Group EUR â‚¬250,00\r\nTour Highlights:\r\nThe Golden age\r\n<br>\r\nThe glorious time of the Marais was during the 17th and 18th centuries. The king Henry IV built the Royal Place, the current Place des Vosges. It became the center of the elegance during this time.\r\n<br>\r\nThat\'s why many aristocrats and wealthy families had settled down in this area. Many private mansions were built, with gorgeous decoration and splendid architecture.\r\n<br>\r\nThe first "salons" were held in the Marais, and became the place to meet wits, elegant ladies, prominent writters and scientists. Thus, Paris made a reputation of capital of sociability.\r\n<br>\r\nFrom decline to historical patrimony\r\n<br>\r\nAt the end of Louis XIV\'s reign in 1715, the Marais was gradually abandonned by the aristocrats. The Royal Court moved to Versailles, the faubourg Saint-Germain and the faubourg Saint-HonorÃ©.\r\n<br>\r\nDuring the 19th century, the Marais became poor and industrious. Workshop were built in the former gardens and courtyards. Hopefully, Haussmann didn\'t destroy it!\r\n<br>\r\nIt\'s only in 1962 that the Marais became officially protected as historical patrimony, and that it\'s rehabilitation has started until nowadays.\r\n<br>\r\nTour Inclusions:\r\nThe private guide, the visit of the private mansions.', 'Tous les jours', 'Marais Tour'),
('', 'Mare e Monti Hiking', 'Corse', '', 625, 0, 'Trekking', 'Mare e Monti\r\nSelf-guided hike\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe road snakes and twirls between cliffs and macchia landscapes along the most spectacular and untamed coastline of our island. The Gulf of Porto and Scandola natural reserve are classed by UNESCO as a site of world beauty. Daily bathing opportunities will make you forget how tired you were. \r\nYou will enjoy a week walking into the wilderness with the Sea, the macchia and Reef as travelling companions. \r\n<br>\r\nLEVEL : Medium | SEASON : printemps-automn | DURATION : 6 days  | PRICE : 625 â‚¬ / person\r\n<br>\r\nProgramme of the trek\r\nLevel : Medium \r\n<br>\r\nDay 1 - Appointment in the morning at the bus station in Ajaccio. Transfer to Evisa. \r\nThe easy The chestnut tree trail lead you to the magnificent natural pool of AÃ¯tone. You spend the night in Evisa. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 2 - You walk down an old mule track to the Spelunca canyon. You follow the valley all the way to the village of Ota. The vegetation changes little by little, from mountain to Mediterranean flora. You spend the night in Ota. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 2 - The path is used to seasonal migrate the livestock to the summer pastures climbed up the Vitrone ravine. The rock walls are eroded in amazing shapes. The Medeterrainen Sea paints the background in blue. After the La Bocca San Petrukbround pass, you walk down to the Bussaglia beach. You spend the night in a hotel near the beach. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 3 - The path winds in the heart of the maquis towards the villages Partinello and Curzu. Then, following the Linu ridge, you can see the gulfs of Porto and Girolata at the same time. You spend the night in a bed in Osani. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 4 - After the long hikes the previous days, this rest day is welcome. A short hike allows you to visit Girolata, protected by an old, small fort and to take advantage of the sea. This village is only accessible by foot or by boat, and itâ€™s also the only anchorage place for the sailors between Carghjese and Calvi! Boat trip to the Nature reserve of Scandola. You spend the night in the gÃ®te of Girolata. NB! No access to the extra baggage this day. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 5 - You cross one of the wildest places of Corsica. There is nothing but the maquis, the granite and the sea to accompany you throughout this part of the hike. You spend the night in Galeria. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 6 - Transfer in the morning to Calvi.\r\n<br>\r\nPRACTICAL INFORMATIONS\r\nPRICE : \r\n625 â‚¬ per person \r\n<br>\r\nACCOMODATION : \r\nGÃ®te, hotel, bedroom \r\n<br>\r\nASSISTANCE :\r\nThe assistance team transports the baggage between the accommodations. You have access to your extra baggage every evening except Evening 5 in Girolata.\r\n<br>\r\nDates 2017 : \r\nFrom 14th of April to 16th of October : every days except Sunday and Monday. \r\n<br>\r\nThe price includes: \r\n- Transportation day 1 and 6 by bus \r\n- Full pension day 1 until breakfast day 6 \r\n- Hike descriptions and map. \r\n- Transportation of baggage day 1 to 5. \r\n<br>\r\nThe price does not include: \r\n- Personal spending during the hike \r\n- Beverages \r\n- Cancelation insurance', 'Everyday', 'Mare e Monti  Hiking'),
('', 'Medieval Paris', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d83998.94740156252!2d2.2773451864780037!3d48.858837635028124!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1f06e2b70f%3A0x40b82c3688c9460!2sParis!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501602108059" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 265, 3, 'Visites', 'During the tour, we will discover three major Gothic monuments of Paris: Notre-Dame de Paris, the Conciergerie and the Sainte-Chapelle. All three are located on the Ile de la Cite in the historical heart of the city just a hundred meters one from another.\r\n\r\nAside from the story of the hunchback, the Cathedral of Notre-Dame impresses its visitors because of its refined architecture, stained glass windows, statues, gargoyles and even secret messages written in its stones. The nearby Conciergerie is the best Parisian example of secular Gothic architecture. At first, the residence of the French kings, centuries before the Louvre or Versailles, it was later turned into a terrible prison, where Queen Marie-Antoinette and hundreds of prisoners spent their last days before being sent to the guillotine. Lastly, we will visit the Sainte-Chapelle skipping the long line at the entrance. Although some people consider the Middle-Ages to be a very dark period in European history, we will see how untrue this judgement might be using as an example the worldâ€™s most impressive medieval stained glass windows of the Sainte-Chapelle.', 'Tous les jours', 'Medieval Paris'),
('', 'Montmartre', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2623.5322478969756!2d2.3408954508569426!3d48.886192879188584!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e432e04c811%3A0xc63ce48b5005548d!2sMontmartre!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501602200507" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 230, 2, 'Visites', 'During this walking tour, you will see all of Montmartreâ€™s major landmarks such as the â€œI love youâ€ wall, Dalidaâ€™s house, the cabaret â€œAu Lapin Agileâ€, the Place du Tertre and its painters, the Sacred Heart basilica. Enjoy the particular atmosphere of this artistic and village-like neighbourhood and take pictures of Montmartreâ€™s postcard views with windmills, vineyards, winding hilly streets and long, steep steps. Although walking up the highest hill in Paris might be hard for some people, you will be rewarded, in the end, with a breath-taking view of the city and its rooftops. You will surely love Montmartre, a typical Parisian neighbourhood, but one which is also very different from the rest of the city. Come and discover why!', 'Tous les jours', 'Montmartre'),
('', 'Montmartre by night tour', 'Paris', '', 189, 2, 'By-night', '\r\nThe Montmartre by Night tour of Paris: the Paris excursion with a difference\r\n<br>\r\nIf youâ€™re in search of a Paris excursion with a difference, our Montmartre by Night tour of Paris, is a must.  From the cosy comfort of your 2CV, youâ€™ll be able to look out on Paris at her finest in her garb of lights! And to make sure that you enjoy a truly sparkling experience, this Paris excursion comes complete with a complimentary bottle of champagne.  \r\nYouâ€™ll begin your Montmartre by Night tour of Paris with a drive along the Avenue des Champs ElysÃ©es to the Arc de Triomphe, before passing by splendidly illuminated monuments such as the Eiffel Tower, Invalides, Louvre and Notre Dame Cathedral.  Your magical night time Paris excursion continues as you wend your way through Montmartre, sipping your glass of bubbly as you take in some of Parisâ€™s best-known nightlife, including the Moulin Rouge and Pigalle district.  Your night tour of Paris culminates â€“ both figuratively and literally â€“ at the SacrÃ© Coeur basilica, from where you can gaze across the City of Lights, bedecked in her finest evening jewels!  For a Paris excursion that will give you a lifetime of memories, a night tour of Paris by 2CV is simply unmissable.\r\n<br>\r\nItinerary of the tour *\r\n\r\nAvenue des Champs ElysÃ©es - Arc de Triomphe - TrocadÃ©ro - Tour Eiffel - Invalides - Pont Alexandre 3 - Petit et Grand Palais - Place de la Concorde - OpÃ©ra Garnier - Place VendÃ´me - Pyramide du Louvre - Ile de la CitÃ© - Notre Dame - Hotel de ville + Montmartre + Moulin Rouge + Pigalle + SacrÃ© Coeur + Bottle of champagne\r\n\r\nUntil 3 people\r\n\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'everyday', 'Montmartre by night tour ');
