('', 'Monuments of Bordeaux', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 265, 2, 'Visites', '\r\n1049/5000\r\nThis tour allows to discover the most famous monuments of Bordeaux. Through it, we will discover the Grand Theater which is located in the heart of the city center as well as the monument of the Girondins and its fountain which risked to be destroyed to be melted during the Second World War! Then we will wear the AllÃ©es de Tourny and their role in the architecture of an 18th century town. Then we will discover Place de la Bourse formerly called the Place Royale, which was built by Louis XV at the beginning of the 18th century.\r\nDuring this visit, we will discover the different habits and French culture, sharing our knowledge and our experience of this country. Finally, we will end the visit by the rue Sainte Catherine which, since the Roman times, is the main street of the city of Bordeaux.\r\nWe hope that a visit like this one will allow you to know more about the history of the city of Bordeaux and will offer you a panorama of the latter which will make you want to discover more ..', 'Tous les jours', 'Monuments of Bordeaux'),
