('', 'Paris Ã©ternel', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499859628969" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 3, 'Bike', 'Guided Bike Tour Paris Eternel\r\nThe goal of this visit is to be charmed. And you will be when you discover historic and contemporary Paris by bicycle with your professional guide.\r\n\r\nStarting out from the futuristic surroundings of Beaubourg, explore the reputable and now-in-style Marais district, home to one of the most beautiful spots in Paris: Place des Vosges.\r\n\r\nA typically delicious cafÃ© awaits you at one of the oldest covered markets in Paris. Your professional guide brings you up to date on the recent scandals of the Buren Columns and the Louvre Pyramid before taking you to where the Celts first settled, the legendary Heart of Paris: lâ€™Ile de la CitÃ©. Then take in Notre Dame on your way to Ile St.Louis â€“ and all its hidden secretsâ€¦\r\n\r\nStops and or sights\r\nCentre Pompidou / Fontaine Stravinsky\r\nHÃ´tel de Sens\r\nVillage St Paul\r\nPlace des Vosges\r\nVictor Hugo House\r\nMarais District / Jewish Quarter\r\nMarchÃ© des Enfants Rouges\r\nRoyal Palace / colonnes de Buren\r\nLouvre Museum and Pyramid\r\nPont-Neuf\r\nIle de la CitÃ© / Notre-Dame\r\nIle Saint-Louis\r\n\r\nINCLUDED IN THE TOUR\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket, ponchor\r\nProfessional National Guide\r\nInsurance\r\nThe price of the visit does not include: -Food and drinks at scheduled stops\r\n\r\nAvailable in English French and German', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'Paris Ã©ternel'),
('', 'Paris by night', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499859628969" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 3, 'Bike', 'Guide Bike Tour Paris By Night\r\nWhen all seems quiet grab your bike because Paris never sleeps.\r\n<br>\r\nLife in Paris never stops. Some parts of the city, like the Marais, might even have more going on at night. Take the bike and follow your guide and discover â€œthe places to beâ€ of the Marais district.\r\n<br>\r\nThen youâ€™ll follow the Seine and marvel at the illuminated splendour of Notre Dame, Pont Neuf, the Louvre, and the Grand Palais, culminating in the spectacular lights (20,000) of the Eiffel Tower. On your return to Beaubourg you take the opposite shore highlighted by the Palais de Chaillot, Place de la Concorde and the Conciergerie.\r\n<br>\r\nSights or Stops:\r\nQuartier du Marais\r\nPlace des Vosges\r\nNotre Dame\r\nIle de la CitÃ©\r\nPlace Dauphine\r\nPont des Arts / Pont Neuf\r\nMusÃ©e dâ€™Orsay\r\nNouvelles Berges de Seine Rive gauche\r\nMusÃ©e du Quai Branly\r\nTour Eiffel\r\nPalais de Chaillot\r\nPont Alexandre III\r\nGrand Palais / Petit palais\r\nLes Invalides\r\nPlace de la Concorde\r\nLe Louvre\r\n<br>\r\nThe price of this visit include\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket, poncho\r\nInsurance\r\nThe price of the visit does not inlcude: Food and drinks at scheduled stops\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in French English and French ', 'Daily from 19 pm ', 'Paris by night'),
('', 'Paris en Seine', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499859628969" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 3, 'Bike', 'Guided Bike Tour Paris en Seine\r\n<br>\r\nTake in the most iconic sights of the capital while following the banks of the Seine (a UNESCO world cultural heritage site).\r\nA unique spectacle is waiting for you!\r\n<br>\r\nWe start on the right bank of the Seine. Our first crossing is the Pont Notre-Dame in our adventure of discovery as we follow Parisâ€™s winding history. From the Notre Dame Cathedral to the Eiffel tower; from the Palais de Chaillot to the Louvre Palace â€“you will enjoy the most beautiful perspectives that offer Paris while your professional guide will allow you to discover prestigious monuments and multiples treasures of the cityâ€¦\r\n<br>\r\nStops and Sight:\r\nCity islands (Ile de la CitÃ©/Notre Dame)\r\nConciergerie / Palais de Justice\r\nPlace Dauphine\r\nPont des Arts / Pont Neuf\r\nMusÃ©e dâ€™Orsay\r\nNouvelles Berges de Seine Rive gauche (Coffee -Break)\r\nMusÃ©e du Quai Branly\r\nEiffel Tower\r\nPalais de Chaillot\r\nAlexandre III Bridge\r\nGrand Palais / Petit palais\r\nLes Invalides\r\nPlace de la Concorde\r\nLes Tuileries / Louvre Museum\r\n<br>\r\nINCLUDED IN THE TOUR\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket, ponchor\r\nProfessional National Guide\r\nInsurance\r\nThe price of the visit does not include: -Food and drinks at scheduled stops\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in English French and German', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'Paris en Seine '),
('', 'Paris Left Bank', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499859628969" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 3, 'Bike', 'Guided bike tour Paris Left Bank\r\nA voyage through the Latin Quarter â€“ the Paris of literature and art.\r\n<br>\r\nThis guided bike tour lets you travel through time. From the ArÃ¨nes de LutÃ¨ce, testimony to the Roman Empire, on to Saint-Germain des PrÃ©s, the centre of the vibrant post-war â€˜New Waveâ€™ culture of intellectuals, artists and ground-breaking film-makers.\r\n<br>\r\nOn this visit youâ€™ll discover Sainte GeneviÃ¨ve and Clovis and the birth of France; the middle ages of the Latin Quarter and its scholars; the contemporary world of the students of the Sorbonne; through the heartland of French cinema; then fashion and the designers who displaced the intellectuals. Itâ€™s all here â€“ including a detour to the elegant jardin de Luxembourg.\r\n<br>\r\nSight and/or Stops\r\n<br>\r\nBeaubourg\r\nCarrefour Saint Paul\r\nPont de la Tournelle\r\nArÃ¨nes de LutÃ¨ce\r\nJardin des Plantes\r\nMosquÃ©e de Paris\r\nQuartier Mouffetard\r\nRue des Ã‰coles\r\nLa Sorbonne/MusÃ©e du Moyen Age\r\nLe PanthÃ©on\r\nLe Jardin du Luxembourg\r\nSaint Sulpice\r\nSaint Germain des PrÃ©s\r\nPlace Saint Michel\r\n<br>\r\nThe price included:\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nInsurance\r\nNot included: Refreshments, snacks and drinks at well-earned breaks\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in French Englisgh and German', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'Paris Left Bank '),
('', 'Paris Populaire', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.7918216304256!2d2.3507548151172935!3d48.8621800083949!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1b991f6245%3A0xd43e49560a39afb7!2s13+Rue+Brant%C3%B4me%2C+75003+Paris!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499859628969" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 3, 'Bike', 'Private Bike Tour Paris Populaire\r\nDiscovering eastern Paris by bike\r\n<br>\r\nUnusual, popular and cosmopolitain â€“ leaving a lasting impression that matches the most iconic sights of Paris.\r\n<br>\r\nOn this original guided bike tour you leave behind the places where the tourists usually go; another side of the most-visited city in the world awaits. Leaving from Beaubourg and going east to where the four revolutions (from 1789 to 1870) were born you will see for yourself how parts of the city and the lives of ordinary people were forever changed. But the area of Belleville never lost its local popular identity and has kept its artisanal and militant character. With its twin, Menilmontant, they form the most cosmopolitain area of Paris.\r\n<br>\r\nYour guide will help you understand why and how this urban evolution came about, while showing you unexpected and little-known spots full of charm like the Canal Saint Martin, the back-streets of a village or the more recent Parc de Belleville.\r\n<br>\r\nSpots\r\n\r\nLa Bastille\r\nQuai de Valmy (le Canal)\r\nQuai de la Loire\r\nParc de la Villette\r\nQuartier de la Mouzaia\r\nParc de Belleville\r\nQuartier Belleville\r\nQuartier Menilmontant\r\nLe PÃ¨re-Lachaise\r\n<br>\r\nThe price of the visit include\r\nBicycle\r\n<br>\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nInsurance\r\nNot included: Refreshments, snacks and drinks at well-earned breaks\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in English French and German\r\n', 'Every day morning or afternoon', 'Paris Populaire '),
('', 'Paris Romantic Tour', 'Paris', '', 179, 2, 'Sightseeing-tour', '\r\nIn search of romantic things to do in Paris? Take our â€œRomantic Parisâ€ tour! \r\n<br>\r\nRomantic Paris, city of lights, lovers and dreams!  Let yourself be seduced by its charm as you explore its hidden streets in an open-top 2CV from Paris Authentic.  Among the most romantic things to do in Paris, our â€œRomantic Parisâ€  will see you wind your way through Montmartre, tracing the steps of the 19th and 20th century artists, to the SacrÃ©-Coeur basilica and the charming Place du Tertre, surely two of the most romantic Paris landmarks!  And you can also cuddle up to that special person as you ride along the Champs ElysÃ©es and by the Eiffel Tower, in the very heart of Paris.  Whether youâ€™re getting married, marking a wedding anniversary or celebrating Valentineâ€™s Day, our â€œRomantic Parisâ€ tour is simply ideal for the occasion.  Whatâ€™s more, we understand that romantic things to do in Paris have to be perfect, so weâ€™ll do everything you could ever wish for to fulfil your heartâ€™s desire.  Take a trip to cloud nine in a Paris Authentic 2CV! \r\n<br>\r\nItinerary of the tour *\r\n<br>\r\nMontmartre - SacrÃ© CÅ“ur - Moulin Rouge - Pigalle - OpÃ©ra Garnier - Place VendÃ´me - Pyramide du Louvre - Place de la Concorde - Pont Alexandre 3 - Avenue des Champs-Ã‰lysÃ©es - Arc de Triomphe - TrocadÃ©ro - Tour Eiffelâ€¦ \r\n<br>\r\n* The itinerary may vary depending on traffic or your desires\r\n<br>\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'Everyday ', 'Paris Romantic Tour'),
('', 'Parisian Day Trip', 'Paris', '', 489, 6, 'Sightseeing-tour', 'Paris tours\r\n<br>\r\nNever seen Paris before? Monuments, museums, gardens, art works, beautiful views, will be presented in this exceptional Paris day trip, in a typical Parisian atmosphere aboard your private traditional French car which offers a great view on all these wonders.\r\n<br>\r\nProgram\r\nTime : 6h30\r\nDetails : Tour in 2CV + museums entrances + rustic meal champÃªtre\r\nInfos We establish the program according to your demand, (the followings are just examples and can be modified if you wish)\r\n<br>\r\nProgram\r\n<br>\r\n10h:\r\n\r\nOur driver will pick you up at your hotel, then you will start an exceptional day! The day will begin by the visit of the famous Cathedral Notre Dame. Next, the Ile de la CitÃ©, located in the middle of the Seine.\r\n<br>\r\nYou can also discover the famous Saint Michel district, the Hotel de Ville, and have a wonderful overview on the banks of the river Seine and the most beautiful bridges of Paris such as the Pont Neuf, the Pont des Arts...\r\n<br>\r\nThen you will take the direction of the Palais du Luxembourg passing by beautiful monuments like the Pantheon, the Senat ...\r\n<br>\r\n11h:\r\n\r\nA walk in the Luxembourg gardens is the best way to relax, in this real haven of greenery and peace in the heart of Paris. You can also admire the famous Palais du Luxembourg from the 16th century.\r\n<br>\r\nThe garden is very flowery and original because it has a French part and another part which is more English. It is embellished by various sculptures that make the garden alive. After this relaxing break, you will see the Louvre with its famous pyramid, the Royal Palace, Church of St. Eustache, the Bourse of Paris, the National Assembly, and the Invalides with its golden roof...\r\n<br>\r\n12h00:\r\n\r\nIn front of the Eiffel Tower, you will have the opportunity to appreciate a traditional French picnic on the Champs de Mars park which offers one of the most beautiful views of the capital with the Effeil Tower and the TrocadÃ©ro in perspective.\r\n<br>\r\nYou will discover the pleasure of a French picnic with traditional baguette, camembert, charcuterie, and of course a bottle of red wine!\r\n<br>\r\n13h30:\r\n\r\nThe tour will continue along the Seine to the famous Place de la Concorde, and then, you will go up the most beautiful avenue in the world: the Champs-ElysÃ©es.\r\n<br>\r\nOn the top of the avenue, the driver will do a break, the time for you to climb to the top of the Arc de Triomphe, where you will enjoy the uncommon panorama.\r\n<br>\r\n14h45:\r\n\r\nConcorde, Madeleine, Opera Garnier, Place VendÃ´me, these are the monuments you will see before the visit of the most charming district of Paris: Montmartre.\r\n<br>\r\nVThanks to the 2CV, you will be dropped off at the top of the Butte Montmartre. You can visit the Basilique du SacrÃ© Coeur, or walk to see the painters of the Place du Tertre, famous for its many artists.\r\n<br>\r\n16h:\r\nAt the end of the day trip, our driver will drop you off at your hotel or in the center of Paris.!\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'Every day', 'Parisian day trip'),
