('', 'Queen\'s secrets in the field of the small trianon', 'Paris', '', 200, 2, 'Visites', 'Tragic heroine? Fashion Icon? Who was the real Marie Antoinette?\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe Petit Trianon is for the queen an intimate place and also a place for parties, shows, meetings. Fleeing the etiquette and protocol of the court, she likes to walk, to entertain. A magical place, beautifully decorated and furnished, we will discover its palace and its English garden. The Petit Trianon inaugurates a new art of living.\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nWe will talk about his childhood in Vienna, his arrival at the court of Versailles in Versailles, his difficulties in the court, but also his insanity inspired by Rose Bertin, his secrets of beauty, his love for Count Fersen and his passion for theater.\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nBeloved and admired, the Queen is first appreciated by the French people. But the revolutionary machine is on its way, the people are agitated. Marie-Antoinette, very coquettish, always spends more and attracts jealousies. The pamphlets of the time portray a queen named "the Austrian", the "nymphomaniac" or the "queen deficit".\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n"The affair of the necklace" soon provoked his fall and the family is soon on their way to the Tuileries ...\r\n', '', 'QUEEN\'S SECRETS IN THE FIELD OF THE SMALL TRIANON'),
('', 'Rennes', 'Normandis/ Bretagne', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d85238.42298078876!2d-1.7586664226541229!3d48.116008776484996!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480ede2fa7d69085%3A0x40ca5cd36e4ab30!2sRennes!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509276690" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 135, 2, 'Visites', 'It is a modern city, now the PrÃ©fecture of the DÃ©partement Ille-et-Vilaine as well as the capital of Brittany with a rich heritage and a long history. It was the headquarters of the Parliament of Brittany whose building remains a symbol of the town. The medieval remains are numerous because Rennes is the city of Brittany with the largest number of half-timbered houses. After the great fire in 1720, the town center was rebuilt in the Classical style. Nowadays, modernity and theMiddle Ages intermingle.\r\n', 'Tous les jours', 'Rennes'),
