('', 'Saint-Malo', 'Normandis/ Bretagne', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d84354.91256031604!2d-2.076864849885583!3d48.64637398540723!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480e81102126bf5d%3A0xf8e97dadb22be12d!2sSaint-Malo!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501508995937" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 135, 2, 'Visites', 'Saint-Malo, which is today a big port and a lively seaside resort, is famous for its bay where many islets were fortified at the time of Vauban in the 17th century. Over the 17th and 18th century, this impregnable site became one of the richest cities in the kingdom of France. This was made possible by the doings of its privateers, ship owners and traders. Bombed in August 1944, it was destroyed to 80%, but its reconstruction gave the city its former appearance. Come and follow the paths of its great figures such as Cartier, Surcouf, Chateaubriand, Duguay-Trouinâ€¦\r\n', 'Tous les jours', 'Saint-Malo'),
('', 'School Group', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.7810262763!2d-0.6563530792514479!3d44.86370644020657!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501768405768" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', '', '', 'School Group'),
('', 'Snacks-Conferences', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d83998.94740156252!2d2.2773451864780037!3d48.858837635028124!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1f06e2b70f%3A0x40b82c3688c9460!2sParis!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501590681392" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 200, 2, 'Visites', '"When Paris sits down to table, it is the whole earth that is moved" Eugene Briffault, 1846.\r\n<br>\r\nIn Paris were born the first great chefs and the first restaurants. In the sumptuous setting of the biggest Parisian gastronomic institutions, we will discover the history and the French culinary art ... The words with the mouth, discover the fine forks and the celebrities who frequented these restaurants .\r\n<br>\r\n+ INTRODUCTION TO THE "GOOD MANNERS" TO THE FRENCH\r\n\r\nAND HISTORY OF FRENCH GASTRONOMY.\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nLearn (or revise!) The codes of good conduct at the table, and savor the pleasures of the French Etiquette! We learn to conjugate our French heritage born at the court of Versailles adapting them to our contemporary way of life.\r\n<br>\r\nOne-and-a-half-hour lessons at the table to learn how to set up the table and honor its guests in the restaurants following the choice.', 'Tous les jours', 'SNACKS-CONFERENCES'),
('', 'Special by night tour', 'Paris', '', 99, 1, 'By-night', 'Our special night tour of Paris: the highlight of your Paris trip!\r\n<br>\r\nIn just an hour, our night tour of Paris will reveal the magic of the French capital at night!  Paris, City of Light, is never more stunning than at night, when she truly lives up to her name, with her illuminated avenues and spot-lit monuments taking on a fairytale dimension.  Thatâ€™s why no Paris trip is complete without a night tour of Paris!  However, we donâ€™t just offer a conventional tour: with Paris Authentic, your night tour of Paris will be undertaken in a red-white and blue, open-topped CitroÃ«n 2CV, with an English speaking Parisian at the wheel!  During your nocturnal Paris trip youâ€™ll be able to see all the highlights of central Paris:  Avenue des Champs ElysÃ©es, Arc de Triomphe, TrocadÃ©ro , Eiffel Tower, Invalides, Pont Alexandre 3, Petit et Grand Palais, Place de la Concorde, OpÃ©ra Garnier, Place VendÃ´me , Louvre Pyramid, Ile de la CitÃ©, Notre Dame Cathedral and HÃ´tel de Ville.  Should you be in search of an even more remarkable night tour of Paris, you can also combine your 2CV tour with a Seine cruise or visit to romantic Montmartre, for a once-in-a-lifetime Paris trip. \r\n<br>\r\nItinerary of the tour *\r\n\r\nAvenue des Champs ElysÃ©es - Arc de Triomphe - TrocadÃ©ro - Tour Eiffel - Invalides - Pont Alexandre 3 - Petit et Grand Palais - Place de la Concorde - OpÃ©ra Garnier - Place VendÃ´me - Pyramide du Louvre - Ile de la CitÃ© - Notre Dame - Hotel de Ville\r\n<br>\r\n* The itinerary may vary depending on traffic or your desires\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'every day ', 'special by night tour');
