('', 'Sturthof Memory and culture site', 'Strasbourg', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2646.1775308250667!2d7.2455616506644!3d48.453123179148!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4793ffb3060a2859%3A0xf3ee75517d91aaf5!2sStruthof%2C+67130+Natzwiller!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501773682127" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Memory and culture site, visit the remains of the Struthof concentration camp, a remarkable place of national remembrance, and continue on to the European Center of the Resistant Deported .', '', 'Sturthof Memory and culture site'),
('', 'Suisse traditionelle', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2797031.759961132!2d5.975299105417573!3d46.79492230243206!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x478c64ef6f596d61%3A0x5c56b5110fcb7b15!2sSuisse!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501845382924" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Lake Geneva Riviera, Montreux, Chillon Castle, Lavaux vineyards of UNESCO class: a prestigious universe of elegance to discover not far from the Mont Blanc.\r\nGruyÃ¨res, the land of "above", a region of medium mountain faithful to its history, its traditions. And why not discover the secrets of making chocolate?', '', 'Suisse traditionelle'),
('', 'Sweet Strasbourg', 'Strasbourg', '', 85, 4, 'French-Gastronomy ', '\r\nWhile discovering the history of Strasbourg, we suggest you to meet local enthusiasts who will make you taste their best sweet specialties.\r\n<br>\r\nThese sweets are an integral part of the Alsatian cuisine and believe us, the Alsatians are attached to their desserts! Eat like the locals and experiment with â€œSweet Strasbourgâ€!\r\n<br>\r\nThe highlights of this visit is to taste the sweet version of the Flammenkuche flambÃ©ed before your eyes, as well as the French pastry!\r\n<br>\r\nThe Highlights\r\nDuring this 4 hours tour of all things sweet, we have selected for you 8 typical tastings that will take place in 7 local shops.\r\n<br>\r\nThroughout this visit, your guide will be happy to share his knowledge about the history and culture of his city while letting you discover the best sights of the old city.\r\n<br>\r\nThe Tastings\r\nThe traditional â€œTarte flambÃ©eâ€ (litteraly â€œFlame Pieâ€) has also its sweet cousin! More than a tradition, it is a ritual for every Alsatian! A delicious Kir CrÃ©mant dâ€™Alsace (sparkling local wine) will compliment your tasting.\r\nThe expertise of Alsace bakers is famous beyond our borders! Try oute the best specialties: Kougelhopf (Alsatian cake) &  Bredele (traditional Christmas biscuits)\r\nLet yourself be surprised by the local flavours of Christianâ€™s chocolates. In summer, refresh your taste buds with a homemade ice-cream from Chez Christian. You will discover local flavours & sometimes some more surprising flavours, such as geranium, which is reminiscent of the flowered balconies of Alsace.\r\nHow can you not succumb to a beautiful pastry?\r\nDiscover the secrets of Alsatian Gingerbread in a pretty little shop in the heart of Strasbourg, the famous Gingerbred Queen Mireille Oster! Hang on, weâ€™ll take your taste-buds on a sensational journey!', 'Everyday', 'Sweet Strasbourg'),
('', 'Tandem skydiving in Corsica', 'Corse', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2980.8513339184506!2d8.891415314840474!3d41.65895398707972!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12da369b78591d59%3A0x400957cdc9d789bd!2sEcole+de+Parachutisme+Du+Valinco+-+Corse+Parachutisme!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499860616980" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 270, 3, 'Skydiving', 'Tandem skydiving in Corsica\r\n \r\n<br>\r\nAfter a briefing with your tandem instructor, which is a Professional skydiver, jump for a 40 seconds freefall between sea and mountain, followed by 4 minutes of descent under canopy..\r\n \r\n<br>\r\nGuarantee Adrenaline Rush !\r\n<br>\r\nMarc LE HELLEY\r\n2 times Vice World Champion in 8-way formation Skydiving RW\r\n5 Championship titles in France 16-way RW (Relative Work)\r\nEuropean Champion 16-way RW\r\nProfessional skydiver Civil Aviation and Youth and Sports\r\nState Certificate\r\nAeronautics\' Medal\r\n16 000 jumps which 4 000 in tandem\r\n<br>\r\nRECOMMANDATIONS\r\nMin age : 12 years and parental advisory\r\nWeight : Min 40 kg | Maxi 90 kg\r\nMedical certificate of no contraindication\r\nto sports practice\r\n<br>\r\n70â‚¬ for the video', 'From June 17 to October 29, 2017  Every days form 9am to 8pm', 'Tandem skydiving in Corsica'),
('', 'Tapas Bar Tour and Tasting in Biarritz', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2895.0171740095407!2d-1.5659127850932235!3d43.48111197156057!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd516b28c5b14807%3A0xe9f341ca388954bc!2s30+Rue+Gambetta%2C+64200+Biarritz!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499860736834" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 69, 2, 'Fun', 'Tapas bar tour and tasting\r\n<br>\r\nLet us take you on a fun and tasty tour in the most dynamic part of town where the locals go to drink wine and eat tapas after a long day in the sunshine. Savor delicious seafood, and many other local delights the Basque Country has to offer along with matching wines. We will go from our favorite local wine bar to Biarritzâ€™s best loved Oyster and Tapas bars.\r\n<br>\r\nThe festive atmosphere of the Biarritz evening scene will remain without a doubt one of your best vacation memories.\r\n<br>\r\nThe package\r\n<br>\r\nPassionate and experienced local guide (French and English speaking)\r\nMultiple tastings of regional products\r\nSmall intimate groups\r\nMeeting point: HÃ´tel Silhouette â€“ 30 Rue Gambetta, 64200 Biarritz\r\nDuration: 1.5 hours\r\n', 'Tuesday, Thursday', 'TAPAS BAR TOUR AND TASTING IN BIARRITZ'),
('', 'Tarte FlambÃ©e Cooking Class', 'Strasbourg', '', 35, 1, 'French-Gastronomy', 'Enjoy your stay in Strasbourg and discover the recipe of the famous flammekueche (â€œTarte FlambÃ©eâ€ in French, litteraly â€œFlame Pieâ€) in order to make it yourself at home & take back a bit of Alsace with you when you leave! We propose, through this cooking class, to immerse yourself in one of the most popular culinary traditions of Alsace.\r\n\r\nThe Gruber is a typical â€œWinstubâ€ of Strasbourg, and is lucky enough to own a traditional â€œTarte FlambÃ©eâ€ oven. You can enjoy the warm atmosphere of the place while cooking and tasting together.\r\n\r\nThe Highlights\r\nDuring this cooking class you will discover savory and sweet versions of the â€œTarte FlambÃ©eâ€. Your tasting will be served with a glass of Alsatian wine or a glass of local beer.\r\n\r\nDuring this experience you will be hosted by one of our â€œflambistesâ€ who will share his secrets with you.', 'Every day', '"Tarte flambÃ©e" Cooking Class'),
('', 'The 3 scenic coastal roads', 'French-Riviera', '', 225, 7, 'Visites', 'During this day, you will discover the most beautiful course of the entire Riviera, where the\r\nAlpes-Maritimes fall into the Mediterranean. Nice and Monaco are the famous "Corniches", the 3 coastal roads that offer the most breathtaking views.You will see the lower coastal road that follows the shore of the Mediterranean, visit the picturesque fishing village of Villefranche, To the middle of the coastal road where Eze is located, one of our most picturesque hill-top villages, and we then drive to the upper coastal road to La Turbie, where you can enjoy the breathtaking view Riviera, visit the glorious Principality of Monaco, take a tour of the famous Formula I racetrack, which leads directly through the city, and stop at the famous Casino Square. Adapted to your personal wishes', 'Tous les jours', 'The 3 scenic coastal roads'),
('', 'The Alsatian Museum', 'Strasbourg', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2639.6032411627366!2d7.748499550671179!3d48.57914742818065!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4796c853348f929d%3A0x3002da53a3f9b850!2sMus%C3%A9e+alsacien!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501586294409" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 200, 2, 'Visites', '', 'Tous les jours', 'The Alsatian Museum'),
('', 'The Capes', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 265, 2, 'Visites', 'At the MarchÃ© des Capucins, known as "Les Capus" for the locals, we will regale our eyes with fresh local fruits, vegetables, meat, fish, cheeses, breads and pastries. Your bilingual guide will help you navigate between stands.tals and sellers, rubbing elbows with local chefs who shop in the morning! In addition to the very good quality food, this market is full of interesting characters, sellers with big mustaches and hands worn by the land to authentic old guys in berets! Our visit to the market is an invitation to the senses and a true French experience.', 'Tous les jours', 'The Capes'),
('', 'The Classical GR20 in 13 days Guided hike', 'Corse', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2968.9340950214773!2d8.72597411484966!3d41.91577547103557!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12da69e85b34e06d%3A0xe9d92b1aa183ac99!2s6+Boulevard+Fred+Scamaroni%2C+20000+Ajaccio!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499860932963" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 1360, 0, 'Trekking', 'The Classical GR20 in 13 days\r\nGuided hike\r\n<br>\r\nThe GR20 crosses the island diagonally following the high granite barrier of mountains that form the natural boundary between the two departments of Corsica. The trail offers some fantastic scenery, along with an insight into the authentic and traditional working mountain community. We may meet the last of the shepherds that still follow the age-old lifestyle of the transhumance, where by they pass the summer months with their flocks on the high fresh airy pastures and the winters down by the coast. \r\n<br>\r\nLEVEL : very athletic | SEASON : summer | DURATION : 14 days  | PRICE : 1360 â‚¬ / person\r\n<br>\r\nProgramme of the trek\r\nNiveau : Very athletic \r\n<br>\r\nDay 1 - Sunday: You meet your guide in Ajaccio early in the morning. Transfer to the Bavella pass. We walk along the alpine variant to pass through the heart of the Bavella massif.  We are surrounded by peaks and ravines and the view is magnificent. Night at the Refuge dâ€™Asinao \r\nDuration: 4h00 / Up : +810m / Down: -410m / 6,7 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 2 - Monday: We take the trail that leads up to the summit of Alcudina (2134m), our first summit above 2000m. The landscape becomes smoother while traversing the Plateau du Cuscionu. Night at the shepherds hut of Bassetta or I Crocci. Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 5h30 / Up : +710m / Down : -900m / 12,3 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 3 - Tuesday: We leave the plateau and joins ArÃªte des statues (the statues ridge). We find our way between these strange granit boulders shaped by the wind. Night at refuge dâ€™Usciolu. \r\nDuration: 4h30 / Up : +630m / Down: -210m / 8,4 km. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 4 - Wednesday: We still walk on the ridge and overlook the Mediterranean sea. This long and great day leads us to the Verde Pass. On the way, we climb Punta Capella (2041 m). Night at the refuge de Prati or at the lodge Col de Verde. Access to the following baggage if night at Col de Verde \r\nDuration: 7h00 / Up : +790m / Down: -1240m / 14,5 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 5 - Thursday: We pass through some idyllic spots and visit remote stone shepherds huts. We walk between the surprising water holes of Pozzi du Renoso and continue easily to our lodge. Night at the lodge of Capanelle. Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 6h00 / Up : +850m / Down: -520m / 18,6 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 6 - Friday: By and old mule track, we arrive at the Palmente pass (1640 m).  We enjoy the magnificent scenery on Diana\'s and Urbino\'s ponds and a beautiful view to the east coast. Descent through Vizzavona beech grove. Night at the lodge of Vizzavona. Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 5h00 / Up : +220m / Down: -890m / 15,3 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 7 - Saturday: We walk up along the Agnone river and reach Punta Muratellu (2141 m). After this long and steep slope, the view on the highest peaks is a good reward for our efforts. We descend to the refuge de lâ€™Onda that we can see far underneath. Night at refuge de l\'Onda \r\nDuration: 6h40 / Up: +1220 m / Down  : -710 m / 11,8 km \r\n<br>\r\nDay 8 - Sunday: Depending on the weather conditions we follow the exposed ridge of Pinzi Corbini (2021m) or we walk down to the Manganellu river that we follow upwards ; Plenty of bathing possibilities. A last steep slope and we join the small refuge de Petra Piana. Night at refuge de Petra Piana \r\nDuration: 5h15 / Up: +900 m / Down: -490 m / 10,2 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 9 - Monday: We first walk up to the Haute Route pass (2206 m) and then we follow the edge that overlooks the Melu and Capitellu lakes. After the  Bocca a e Porte notch (2225 m) we go down a wild valley to the refuge de Manganu and continue easily to the shepherds hut Vaccaghja.  Night at shepherds hut Vaccaghja. \r\nDuration: 6h00 / Up : +630m / Down: -890m / 11,3 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 10 - Tuesday: We walk easily through a beech grove and reach the Ninu lake surrounded by green lawns. From the top of Capu a u Tozzu (2007m) we have a fantastic panorama to the Niolu valley and the next stages. Night at the lodge Castel de Vergio. Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 5h30 / Up : +350m / Down: -550m / 13,8 km \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 11 - Wednesday: We penetrate the volcanic massif of Monte Cintu-Paglia Orba. The first part of the stage is easy along the Golu river. After the Foggiale pass the terrain becomes steeper and looser. Good bathing possibilities at the end of the stage.  Night at Shepherds hut Ballone or at refuge de Tighjettu. \r\nDuration: 6h00 / Up : +730m / Down: -720m / 13,4 km \r\n  <br>\r\n \r\n 	  Day 12 - Thursday: An impressive and strenuous day in high mountains. We walk up the Crucetta valley to the top of pointe des Eboulis (2600m). Depending of the weather and the physical shape of the group we climb the Monte Cintu (2706m), highest mountain of Corsica.  Night at the lodge Le Chalet at Ascu Stagnu. Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 6h00 / Up : +850m / Down: -520m / 8,9 km \r\n<br>\r\nDay 13 - Friday: A short but steep slope leads us to the Muvrella pass and we descend the deep Spasimata valley surrounded by sharp peaks. Some exposed passages on slabs are equipped with chains. The Mediterranean plants appear again, temperature rises and the trail flattens out; a sweet end off our trip. Arrival in Bonifatu and transfer to Calvi.  Access to the following baggage \r\nDuration: 7h00 / Up : +680m / Down: -1530m / 9,6 km \r\n  \r\n<br>\r\nPRACTICALS INFORMATIONS:\r\nPRICE : \r\n1290 â‚¬ per person \r\nGroup  from 6 to 12 persons per guide \r\n<br>\r\nACCOMODATION : \r\nIn refuges, sheepfolds and shelters \r\n<br>\r\nTRAINING : \r\nBy a mountain guide (groupe de 12 personnes maximum par accompagnateur) \r\n<br>\r\nFOLLOWING BAGGAGE : \r\nYou must always carry in your rucksack hot clothing, a rainwear, one gourd, an emergency case and your personal objects without forgetting part of the picnic. The baggage of assistance (the following baggage) is transferred by our assistance which you find certain evenings with lodgings accessible by road. It contains  the businesses necessary to your stay (does not have to exceed 12 kg). \r\n<br>\r\nDepartures 2017 : \r\nEvery sunday from the end of May to the middle of September \r\n\r\n<br>\r\nThis price includes: \r\n- The take in charge in the place of the appointment \r\n-  Transfers \r\n-  The full board \r\n-  The training by a mountain guide \r\n-  The transfer of the luggage between the accommodations (as detailed in â€œAssistanceâ€) \r\n  <br>\r\nThis price does not include/understand: \r\n- Personal expenses, drinks \r\n- The insurances cancellation and repatriation \r\n- All is not written in "this price include"', 'Everyday', 'The Classical GR20 in 13 days Guided hike'),
('', 'The GR20 North part in 6 days Self-guided hike', 'Corse', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2968.9340950214773!2d8.72597411484966!3d41.91577547103557!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12da69e85b34e06d%3A0xe9d92b1aa183ac99!2s6+Boulevard+Fred+Scamaroni%2C+20000+Ajaccio!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499861108628" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 590, 0, 'Trekking', 'The GR20 North part in 6 days\r\nSelf-guided hike\r\n<br>\r\n\r\nThe GR 20 Trail follows the mountains line that separate the island in two. The northern part is more alpine and demanding. The landscapes along the way are breathtaking, awesome and versatile, the Mediterranean sea always featured in the background. \r\n<br>\r\nLEVEL : very athletic | SEASON : summer | DURATION : 6 days  | PRICE : 590 â‚¬ / person\r\n<br>\r\nPROGRAMME\r\nNiveau : very athletic \r\n<br>\r\nDay 1: Ajaccio Tattone - Petra Piana \r\nAppointment in the morning in Ajaccio. After the transfer to Tattone, you start your hike on the GR20 by walking up the valley of Manganellu. You spend the night in tent at Petra Piana. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 2: Petra Piana- Vaccaghja \r\nShort morning climb to the pass at 2206 m. You continue along the ridges overlooking the lakes of Melu Capitellu to access the breach of Bocca a e Porte (2225 m), the highest passage of the GR 20. You spend the night in tent in Vaccaghja. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 3:  Vaccaghja - Vergio \r\nContinuing your journey, you cross a small beech forest. Stop at Lake Ninu, one of the "pearls" of the Corsican mountains, a paradise for horses that grasses there. Walking down the forest to Vergio. You spend the night in Hotel Castel di Vergio \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 4:  Vergio - Ballone \r\nChange of scenery. You enter the volcanic massif of the Grande BarriÃ¨re and climb up the high valley of Golo to the pass of Foggiale. You spend the night in tents to the bergeries Ballone. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 5: Ballone - Ascu Stagnu \r\nThe hikeâ€™s most outstanding experience with the most difficult assage of the week. This is a great moment of the GR20. You spend the night at Hotel Ascu Stagnu. \r\n  <br>\r\nDay 6: Ascu - Bonifatu \r\nBy a short and steep ascent you reach the pass of Muvrella. You leave the mountain world and dive into the canyon Spasimata. The Mediterranean atmosphere is slowly increasing. Arriving Bonifatu, and transfer to Calvi. \r\n<br>\r\nPRICE : \r\n590 â‚¬ per person \r\n<br>\r\nACCOMODATIONS : \r\nIn refuges, bergeries and gÃ®tes. \r\n<br>\r\nFOLLOWING BAGGAGE : \r\nYou must always carry in your rucksack hot clothing, a rainwear, one gourd, an emergency case and your personal objects without forgetting part of the picnic. The baggage of assistance (the following baggage) is transferred by our assistance which you find certain evenings with lodgings accessible by road. It contains  the businesses necessary to your stay (does not have to exceed 12 kg). \r\n<br>\r\nDepartures 2017 : \r\nAll sundays from the 28th of May to the 17th of September included \r\n<br>\r\nThe price includes: \r\n- Transfers Ajaccio- Tattone and Bonifatu-Calvi by bus/taxi \r\n- Full pension from Day 1 up and including breakfast Day 6 \r\n- Day-to-day descriptions and maps IGN \r\n- Baggage transfer from Ajaccio to Calvi \r\n<br>\r\nThe price does not include: \r\n\r\n- Beverages \r\n- Moutiai Guide \r\n- Annulation assurance and assistance \r\n', 'Everyday', 'The GR20 North part in 6 days Self-guided hike'),
('', 'The hill-villages of the eastern RivieraÂ ', 'French-Riviera', '', 225, 7, 'Visites', 'Enjoy a wonderful visit to the Alpes-Maritimes, the finals of the European Alps that fall directly into the Mediterranean between Nice and Menton forming magnificent bays and offering spectacular views.\r\nThe first stop of the tour will be in the beautiful hill village of Eze. Many narrow alleys lead to the exotic garden on the top of the village. This sarcastic bastion of the past has become one of the highlights of the CÃ´te d\'Azur. You will appreciate this very special place with its very medieval atmosphere.\r\nFrom Eze, we will take the superior coastal road to La Turbie, where we will make a magnificent photo-stop. In clear days you will have a view of almost all the French Riviera of Menton up to the Esterel mountain range.\r\nThe road takes us to the mountains where, after 20 minutes by car, we will arrive in the village of Peille. Not far from the buzzing coast, you find a completely different French Riviera where the weather is almost immobile. Explore this unique medieval village on foot and enjoy a breathtaking view. You certainly will not find many tourists here during your visit.\r\n\r\nFrom Peille, we take the very panoramic route through the mountains towards another jewel of the region: St Agnes. It is considered one of the most beautiful villages in France and is in a very strategic position above the coast of Menton. St Agnes is right on the Maginot line, a vast fortification of inter-war years right on the Italian / French border.\r\nOur way back to the coast will lead us to a short scenic walk through the Principality of Monaco.\r\nOf course, this tour can be adapted to your personal wishes', 'Tous les jours', 'The hill-villages of the eastern RivieraÂ '),
('', 'The Mont-Saint-Michel', 'Normandis/ Bretagne', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d21097.868007715366!2d-1.5462694762071663!3d48.624513633337656!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480ea8d67c9ceeb3%3A0xc5834ce47e0dc3fe!2s50170+Le+Mont-Saint-Michel!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501508882204" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 150, 2, 'Visites', 'Letâ€™s discover this wonderful place which is an island again thanks to the rehabilitation of its former maritime characterâ€¦ At the foot of the Benedictine Abbey, founded in 966, a little village developed. It was once much frequented by the pilgrims wishing to pray Archangel Michael. It is now one of the most popular touristic places in France. We shall use the indirect paths and shortcuts to reach the Â«Â MarvelÂ Â»!\r\n', 'Tous les jours', 'The Mont-Saint-Michel'),
('', 'The Mont-Saint-Michel 3h', 'Normandis/ Bretagne', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d21097.868007715366!2d-1.5462694762071663!3d48.624513633337656!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480ea8d67c9ceeb3%3A0xc5834ce47e0dc3fe!2s50170+Le+Mont-Saint-Michel!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501508882204" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 180, 3, 'Visites', 'Letâ€™s discover this wonderful place which is an island again thanks to the rehabilitation of its former maritime characterâ€¦ At the foot of the Benedictine Abbey, founded in 966, a little village developed. It was once much frequented by the pilgrims wishing to pray Archangel Michael. It is now one of the most popular touristic places in France. We shall use the indirect paths and shortcuts to reach the Â«Â MarvelÂ Â»!\r\n', 'Tous les jours', 'The Mont-Saint-Michel 3h'),
('', 'The Mysteries of Wine in Bordeaux', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 3, 320, 'Visites', 'This visit begins at the Place Royale, home of the famous wine classification of 1855. Here, we will learn the history of the Bordeaux port and its role in the wine trade, from the Middle Ages to the In modern times.\r\nThen, we will jump in the modern tram of the city to visit the Museum of Wine and Trade, housed in a wine cellar whose construction dates back to the 18th century, it was originally the home of a wines. We will dig the history of the wines of Bordeaux, as well as the role of the traders in the preparation and distribution of these wines. After a guided tour through the exhibitions of the museum, we will have the opportunity to taste delicious Bordeaux wines in the museum\'s tasting room.\r\nThen we will walk through the Chartrons district, the historic district of the city used by wine merchants and barrel makers 300 years ago. This neighborhood is now a chic neighborhood of the city with its cafes and market places. The Chartrons are an imitation of the Marais district in Paris because of its atypical charm. We will see some old cellars, some of them measuring 300 meters long and were built to age and assemble Bordeaux wines. Today, we will see that they are redeveloped in apartments, shops, art galleries and universities!\r\nFinally, we will conclude this visit with an additional tasting in an adorable wine bar in the heart of the Chartrons district, with a wide selection of Bordeaux wines. This will provide a relaxing and entertaining conclusion to our visit.\r\nThe flavors, colors and history of the Bordeaux wine will become truly alive for you in this visit!', 'Tous les jours', 'The Mysteries of Wine in Bordeaux'),
('', 'The secrets of the old town', 'Marseille', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d185895.01266426005!2d5.264709552713976!3d43.28055461781579!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12c9bf4344da5333%3A0x40819a5fd970220!2sMarseille!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501582322428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 150, 2, 'Visites', 'The tour begins at the old port, in front of the Hotel de Ville.\r\nThe town hall of Marseille dates from the 17th century and despite its baroque facade and pretty door, the entrance is made from behind.\r\nIf its architecture differs from the other buildings of the port quay, it is because it was spared by the Nazi destruction.', 'Tous les jours', 'The secrets of the old town'),
('', 'The specialized and artisanal tour', 'French-Riviera', '', 225, 7, 'Visites', 'The CÃ´te d\'Azur is not only rich in magnificent and famous places but also with regard to its local products: wine, olive oil, goat cheese, candied fruits, honey, socca, pissaladiÃ¨re, lavender, violets , Perfumes, pottery, bubbles ...\r\nEnjoy a full day that will take you to some of the most beautiful villages on the CÃ´te d\'Azur, which are also known for the production of these specialties. This tour is also very fun for children.\r\nDepending on your interests, I will suggest an itinerary that could include a wine tasting and / or olive oil, a visit to a goat farm that produces cheese, a visit to a perfume factory where you Learn all about perfume ...\r\nChoose 3 of these locations:\r\nNice ... for its specialized daily market (except Mondays) where you can taste our delicious Socca (a crepe of chickpeas), the PissaladiÃ¨re (onion pizza) and all kinds of other local specialties\r\nAntibes ... for its specialized daily market (except Mondays) where you can taste the Socca and all kinds of spreads made from local products\r\nTourrettes-sur-Loup ... when it comes to goat cheese, wine, olive oil and specialties in violets\r\nBiot ... for its wonderful bubble glass production. You can see how they blow the glass as they did a few centuries ago\r\nSt Jeannet ... for a visit to a local wine cellar (small supplement for wine tasting)\r\nValauris ... for his pottery\r\nGourdon ... for its small field of colored lavender (only in June / July)\r\nGrasse or Eze ...... for their perfume factories\r\n\r\nPont-sur-Loup ... for its fruit and candied chocolate factory', 'Tous les jours', 'The specialized and artisanal tour'),
('', 'The wine route of Alsace', 'Strasbourg', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1360425.0721941083!2d6.4133614531184!3d48.243583206433996!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x479146a3db7796bf%3A0x10a5fb99a3724e0!2sAlsace!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501773471823" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', ' \r\nThe most famous gastronomic route in France ! History, vineyards, picturesque villages, castles, wine cellars for tasting and good restaurants â€¦\r\n <br>\r\nSuggestions\r\n <br>\r\nRosheim, Boersch, Ottrott, Heiligenstein, Barr, Mittelbergheim,\r\nGertwiller, Kintzheim, Obernai, Bergheim, RibeauvillÃ©, Hunawihr, Riquewihr, Kaysersberg, Eguisheim, Turckheim  ...', '', 'The wine route of Alsace'),
('', 'Undiscover Paris Tour', 'Paris', '', 179, 2, 'Sightseeing-Tour ', '\r\nDiscover Paris in a 2CV with your English-speaking Paris tour guide\r\n<br>\r\nSo you think you know Paris? Discover Paris differently with Paris Authentic, as your Paris tour guide drives you in a 2CV through the narrow, lesser-known streets of the French capital.  Off the beaten track, youâ€™ll discover aspects of Paris that you never knew existed!  Thanks to your English-speaking Paris tour guide, youâ€™ll discover Parisâ€™s many poetic delights, from the superb architectural beauty of the Place des Vosges, to the tiny port hidden close to the Bastille, and the 1st century gallo-romain amphitheatre, les ArÃ¨nes de LutÃ¨ce. But most importantly, in the company of your knowledgeable Paris tour guide, youâ€™ll discover the Paris where Parisians love to stroll, play petanque, or simply take time out to relax.   If youâ€™re looking to escape the everyday tourist traps, then climb into one of Paris Authenticâ€™s tricolour CitroÃ«n 2CVs, and let yourself be spirited away to magical, mysterious, real Paris! \r\n<br>\r\nItinerary of the tour *\r\n\r\nPlace des Vosges - Passage Sully - Village Saint Paul - le Marais - Port de l\'Arsenal - Bastille - Ile Saint Louis - Institut du Monde Arabe - Montagne Sainte GeneviÃ¨ve - Grande MosquÃ©e de Paris - ArÃ¨nes de LutÃ¨ce - Butte aux cailles - CitÃ© Florale... \r\n<br>\r\nPICK UP IN PARIS CENTER : FROM YOUR HOTEL OR ADDRESS IN PARIS CENTER\r\nTHE DRIVERS : FUN, PARISIAN, PROFESSIONAL & ENGLISH SPEAKING\r\nCITROEN 2CV CAR : CONVERTIBLE & TRANSPARENT ROOF', 'Every day', 'Undiscover Paris Tour'),
