('', 'Valais lâ€™autre cote du Mont Blanc', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d706233.6092884028!2d7.062668504108156!3d46.2556937686296!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x478f229bea7f9a17%3A0x100ff884018d860!2sValais%2C+Suisse!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501845350286" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'The Swiss side of the Mont Blanc, a country so close but a culture more oriented towards a rural life faithful to traditions still very alive. The opportunity to see superb villages hanging on the mountain.\r\nThe Col du Grand Saint Bernard, a superb, wild pass or history marks this millenary passage. Sion, a medieval town dominated by two fortified hills.\r\nNot to mention the most beautiful museum in the region: the internationally renowned Giannada Foundation in Martigny.', '', 'Valais lâ€™autre cote du Mont Blanc'),
('', 'Vallee dâ€™Aoste', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d713013.1058740806!2d6.808605092548278!3d45.72693445161535!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4788ded6c5aff5a7%3A0x5625987c799cd59b!2sVall%C3%A9e+d&#39;Aoste%2C+Italie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501845101309" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'In Italy just across the tunnel of the Mont Blanc exists one of the most beautiful valleys of the Alps: a very close Italy offering in view of very beautiful villages with exceptional architecture and surprising castles.\r\nRoman ruins, castles, churches, medieval chapels, Romanesque cloisters, museums are all unsuspected treasures to discover. Enough to fill beautiful days.', '', 'Vallee dâ€™Aoste'),
('', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Classiques', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d177597.06585072956!2d6.7885314374447185!3d45.93221610055099!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47894c062dfe2ee7%3A0x408ab2ae4baa380!2sChamonix-Mont-Blanc!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501843026401" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Cable cars and small trains: Sumptuous landscapes. An exceptional natural heritage.\r\nKnow how to take a look at the striking beauty of the mythical mountains that make up the Mont Blanc massif.\r\nUnderstand the formation and transformation of a glacier.\r\nDiscover the fantastic history of those who built the ski lifts.\r\n<br>\r\nVisit of Chamonix. A walk by roads and streets in Chamonix to go back the time of the rich history of this village become a prestigious station.', '', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Classiques'),
('', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Insolites', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d177597.06585072956!2d6.7885314374447185!3d45.93221610055099!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47894c062dfe2ee7%3A0x408ab2ae4baa380!2sChamonix-Mont-Blanc!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501843026401" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Discover the burials of the mountaineers who have made the history of the mountain through the cemeteries of Chamonix and ArgentiÃ¨re.', '', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Insolites'),
('', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Singulieres', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d177597.06585072956!2d6.7885314374447185!3d45.93221610055099!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47894c062dfe2ee7%3A0x408ab2ae4baa380!2sChamonix-Mont-Blanc!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501843026401" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Chamonix: from the Belle Epoque to the Roaring Twenties. :\r\nDiscover a unique architectural heritage, sometimes extravagant, but exceptional.\r\nPalaces, old hotels, resort villas are astounding testimonies of this emerging period of a more mundane tourism.\r\n<br>\r\nChamonix and its painters: yesterday and today\r\nGoing together to the museum, in private collections, in search of painters who also have the paintings of today.\r\n<br>\r\nArchitecture and town planning from the 1950s to the present:\r\nUnderstand the evolution of a modern and contemporary architecture in the heart of this ancient village and resort.', '', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Singulieres'),
('', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Typiques', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d177597.06585072956!2d6.7885314374447185!3d45.93221610055099!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47894c062dfe2ee7%3A0x408ab2ae4baa380!2sChamonix-Mont-Blanc!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501843026401" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Vallorcine:\r\nWalk in this village out of time where farms and "raccards" are the testimonies of the Walser culture.\r\n<br>\r\nServoz - Les Houches:\r\nGo to meet a past and present rural world.\r\n<br>\r\nHamlets and chapels:\r\nA stunning bus and walk in the valley, off the beaten track. Rediscover the ancestral life and beliefs of our elders.', '', 'Vallee de Chamonix Visites Typiques'),
('', 'Vallee du Giffre', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d708948.3202509595!2d5.863210308888751!3d46.044528060055356!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x478c09f4796a177d%3A0x308ab2ae4b92a20!2sHaute-Savoie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501844702883" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'SamoÃ«ns:\r\nAuthentic village, rich of a strong history and a tradition of unique stone sculpture in this mountainous region. The pleasure is in discovering a village and a valley with rich and varied rural and religious heritage.\r\nSixt:\r\nA village lost in a wild valley. An astonishing apparition that this village ranked among the most beautiful in France, whose heart is made up of an abbey set dating back to the Middle Ages.\r\nHorseshoe :\r\nAdmire the breathtaking circus of the Fer Ã  Cheval: huge rock amphitheater 4 to 5 km wide. The biggest alpine mountain circus.', '', 'Vallee du Giffre'),
('', 'Versailles', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d42045.534755328285!2d2.084158984299696!3d48.80391922838278!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e67db475f420bd%3A0x869e00ad0d844aba!2sVersailles!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499861259381" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 8, 'Bike', 'Private Tour Versailles by bike\r\nA magnificent voyage by bike to the city of the â€˜Roi-Soleilâ€™ (the Sun King â€“ Louis XIV)\r\n<br>\r\nLeaving from our Agency in Beaubourg (2 steps from Centre Pompidou), your guide will bring you and your bicycles to the station where you will board a train for Versailles. Once arrived, you will cross through the royal city, its markets and wide avenues to the parc du ChÃ¢teau where your guide will recount the lives of the inhabitants of the Trianons before Marie Antoinette decided to make it her preffered place of residence. After lunch your guide will show you through the la Galerie des Glaces (the Hall of Mirrors) and the Grands Appartements.\r\n<br>\r\nThe return to Paris can be by bicycle or by train.\r\n<br>\r\nSights and Stops\r\nLa Vieille ville\r\nLe marchÃ©\r\nParc de Versailles (Hameau, Les Trianons, Grand Lac, Les Jardins...)\r\nPause dÃ©jeuner\r\nVisit of Versailles\'s Palace\r\nBack to Paris by train\r\n<br>\r\nThe price of this visit include\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nInsurance\r\nNot included: Refreshments, snacks and drinks at well-earned breaks\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in French English and German', ' Full day 8 hours', 'Versailles'),
('', 'Versailles skip-the-line', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d42045.58217191485!2d2.084073193686397!3d48.80386267004899!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e67db475f420bd%3A0x869e00ad0d844aba!2sVersailles!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501602528474" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 320, 5, 'Visites', 'This tour will introduce you to the French history of the XVII and XVIII centuries. During this period France was at its apogee as the French kings were the most powerful European monarchs. You will learn about the Sun-King Louis the XIV and the guillotined queen Marie-Antoinette, hear the stories about the French Revolution and absolute monarchy, and discover the French gardens and the Hall of Mirrors. After visiting the palace with miraculous Kingâ€™s Grand Apartments and the breath-taking Hall of Mirrors, we will take a short walk to the most beautiful parts of the Versailles gardens.\r\n<br>\r\nVersailles is located 20 km west of Paris, a short trip by the suburb train RER. After the tour you are welcome to stay in Versailles to explore the rest of the royal domain on your own.', 'Tous les jours', 'Versailles skip-the-line'),
('', 'Versailles Tour', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d42045.534777149216!2d2.084073149421088!3d48.803919202354855!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e67db475f420bd%3A0x869e00ad0d844aba!2sVersailles!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501584185768" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 200, 2, 'Visites', '', 'Tous les jours', 'Versailles Tour'),
('', 'Via Ferrata', 'French-Riviera', '', 280, 3, 'Via-Ferrata', 'Via ferrata\r\nIf youâ€™re searching for a sport activity to get a thrill in Nature on the French Riviera, you should try the via ferrata! Itâ€™s a good way to approach big walls even without being an experienced climber. The different spots around Nice, like Peille, Puget Theniers or Tende are just perfect to discover this amazing mixing between hiking and rock climbing.\r\n<br>\r\nThanks to your guideâ€™s advice, youâ€™ll learn safely the different techniques you need to master to have fun on the amazing vias of the Alpes Maritimes. You will be able to climb on big cliffs equipped with ladders, you will cross from one cliff to the other thanks to monkey bridges or zip lines.\r\n<br>\r\nGear: All the necessary equipment will be provided and will respond to high safety standards: helmets, harnesses with specific lanyards, pulleys.\r\n\r\n', 'Monday to Friday', 'Via Ferrata'),
('', 'Vignoble Bordelais', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.7810262763!2d-0.6563530792514479!3d44.86370644020657!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501768505424" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', '', '', 'Vignoble Bordelais'),
('', 'Vincennes by bike', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2626.5535527948305!2d2.4341001151158888!3d48.82857911076028!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e672c3dd5a43dd%3A0xd605987f92436ded!2sBois+de+Vincennes!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499861403859" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 280, 8, 'Bike', 'Private Tour Vincennes by bike\r\nThe Bois de Vincennes by bike: Nature and history meet â€“ two steps from Paris.\r\n<br>\r\nExperience the enchanting flora and wildlife of the 995 hectares of the bois de Vincennes by bike, just a few steps from Paris. And then explore the magnificent ChÃ¢teau de Vincennes. It was built in the 14th century under the initiative of Charles V and is one of the largest and most well preserved castles of Europe, a true symbol of the heritage of France.\r\n<br>\r\nWith your National Guide you will go back in time and relive the history lived and the secrets hidden within the walls of the ChÃ¢teau de Vincennes.\r\n<br>\r\nSights and/or Stops:\r\nLe Parc Floral de Paris / Jardin Insolite\r\nLa plaine de Bercy\r\nLa Tourelle? Lâ€™allÃ©e Royale\r\nLa plaine Saint-Hubert\r\nLâ€™Ecole Du Breuil\r\nLe Jardin dâ€™Agronomie Tropicale\r\nL\'hippodrome de Vincennes\r\nLa Porte Jaune\r\nLe Polygone\r\nLe quartier Carnot\r\nLa Grande Pagode abritant lâ€™Institut International Bouddhique\r\nLes lacs de Saint-MandÃ©, de Daumesnil, de Gravelle, et celui des Minimes\r\nLe ChÃ¢teau de Vincennes\r\n<br>\r\nThe price of this visit include:\r\nBicycle\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nAccessories: helmet, basket\r\nInsurance\r\nNot included: Refreshments, snacks and drinks at well-earned breaks\r\n<br>\r\nAvailable in English French and German', 'Every day ', 'Vincennes by bike'),
('', 'Viree culturelle en Piemont', 'Haute-Savoie', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d713013.1058740806!2d6.808605092548278!3d45.72693445161535!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x4787743b019db167%3A0xbcc7b8edf2123bff!2sPi%C3%A9mont%2C+Italie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501845232770" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 0, 0, 'Visites', 'Not so far the Piedmont is accessible in a short time.\r\nTurin, a remarkable baroque town, remains the exciting demonstration of a common history in the Savoy region: churches, castles, arcaded streets are all rich testimonies of the former Savoyard capital.\r\nThe valley of Suze, the royal palaces, the extraordinary Sacra San Michele are so many surprises to discover.', '', 'Viree culturelle en Piemont'),
('', 'Visit a surfboard workshop in Biarritz', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2626.5535527948305!2d2.4341001151158888!3d48.82857911076028!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e672c3dd5a43dd%3A0xd605987f92436ded!2sBois+de+Vincennes!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499861532892" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 35, 2, 'Sightseeing-Tour', '\r\nSurfboard workshop visit\r\n<br>\r\nBiarritz is one of the most famous surf destinations in Europe with the first surfers gracing the wave filled beaches in the 1950â€™s. Since then, surfing has become more than just a sport in Biarritz but a way of living and the locals do their very best to incorporate surfing into their lives in any way possible.\r\n<br>\r\nShaping your own surf board is considered one of the most humbling experiences a surfer can have and is considered an art form in many ways.\r\n<br>\r\nBiarritz by locals offers you the opportunity to visit a local shaping room where you will learn about surfing history in Biarritz, the foundations of shaping a surfboard and you will be given the opportunity to experience first hand the tools and methods used in shaping a board.\r\n<br>\r\nAfter your visit, if you are interested, speak to our guide about shaping your own board while you are in Biarritz.\r\n<br>\r\nThe package\r\n<br>\r\nBilingual and professional shaper\r\nGroup size 2 to 8 guests\r\nMeeting point: 10 allÃ©e du samadet, 64600 ANGLET\r\nDuration: 1,5 hours', 'Monday, Wednesday, Friday', 'VISIT A SURFBOARD WORKSHOP IN BIARRITZ');
