('', 'Visit Gourmande Head to Head Deluxe', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d90493.5897621176!2d-0.6563530576604518!3d44.86382811572675!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527e8f751ca81%3A0x796386037b397a89!2sBordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501509812428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 420, 3, 'Visites', 'This tour focuses on tasting the sumptuous flavors of Bordeaux with scenic and historical walks linking our tastings. We will have the opportunity to visit one of the most famous and old cheese dairy in Bordeaux, as well as its vaulted cellars for the preservation of cheese, dating from the 15th century. Here we will find a treasure of cheeses that slowly takes on age. Here, a treasure of cheeses is offered to us, slowly taking age during their maturity period, this aging process being explained by one of their expert employee. We will taste three cheeses and enjoy the atmosphere of the old underground cellars.\r\nThen, we visit a Bordeaux society known worldwide for the rebirth of the canelÃ©s, typically regional dessert, originally prepared by the nuns for school children. We will learn the history of this traditional dessert and why its creation in Bordeaux has a link with wine! We will relax by enjoying this sweetness accompanied by a hot drink.\r\nTo finish, we will end with the joy of a wine tasting. A small wine bar will welcome us in its sunny courtyard where we taste three Bordeaux wines. Each one has its unique style, selected and presented for us, by its sommelier.', 'Tous les jours', 'Visit Gourmande Head to Head Deluxe'),
