('', 'Visit of a Basque Vineyard', 'Biarritz', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2899.323252785527!2d-1.686704085096556!3d43.39117257735384!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd510e064799f6f1%3A0x406ba19a96f0439d!2s5bis+Chemin+des+Blocs%2C+64500+Ciboure!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499861751019" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 55, 2, 'Sightseeing-Tour', '\r\nVisit of a Basque vineyard\r\n<br>\r\nMeet at the cellar, located in Socoa, in the former gunpowder magazine, which dates from the end of the 17th century, to discover the history of the creation of the Egiategia vineyard. Emmanuel Poirmeur (winegrower and agronomist) is at the origin of a unique underwater vinification process in the world; In fact, the winemaking takes place 15 meters deep in the bay of Saint Jean de Luz where all the conditions are met to create a second fermentation that will reveal all the aromas of the wine.\r\n<br>\r\nWe propose you a visit of the vineyards located a few kilometers with an impregnable view on the sea to discover the cellar where all the explanations on this innovative concept will be given to you.\r\n<br>\r\nThe visit will end on the terrace with sea view with a tasting of the wines of the property, accompanied by local products (oysters, Bayonne ham, Basque cake).\r\n<br>\r\nDo not miss this unique experience in this atypical place.\r\n<br>\r\nThe package\r\n<br>\r\nLocal and bilingual guide\r\nWine tasting and local products.\r\nSmall groups of up to 8 people.\r\nDurÃ©e : 1.5 hours\r\nMeeting point: Â« Egiategia Â» 5Bis Chemin des Blocs, 64500 Ciboure', 'Tuesday and Thursday only', 'VISIT OF A BASQUE VINEYARD'),
('', 'Visiting Marseille', 'Marseille', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d185895.01266426005!2d5.264709552713976!3d43.28055461781579!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12c9bf4344da5333%3A0x40819a5fd970220!2sMarseille!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501582322428" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 150, 2, 'Visites', 'This guided tour offers a general overview of the second French city.\r\nDiscover its remarkable monuments and its authentic character.\r\nThe tour begins at the Vieux-Port under the OmbriÃ¨re Foster.\r\nThe old port of Marseilles has a central place in the city and has been the heart of its economic activity since antiquity until the industrial revolution. Renovated in 2013 it is today the best place to start the discovery of the city.', 'Tous les jours', 'Visiting Marseille'),
('', 'Weekly Food Tour', 'Strasbourg', '', 49, 2, 'French-Gastronomy', '\r\nWould you like to discover Strasbourg and its food culture, but you have only a few hours to spare?\r\n<br>\r\nWe offer a gourmet tasting-tour lasting 2Â½ hours, which will take you past the iconic Notre-Dame Cathedral and through famous Petite France, stopping to enjoy typical culinary specialties from our region! Fully immerse yourself in local Strasbourg life.\r\n<br>\r\nAccompanied by a tour guide, your journey will begin in the Place de la CathÃ©dral at 14:30. We would advise you to eat only a very light lunch before the tour, to make the most of the tasting experience!\r\n<br>\r\nTastings include:\r\n<br>\r\nTarte FlambÃ©e and Alsace wine\r\nKougelhopf cake\r\nAlsatian cheese\r\nPretzels\r\nGingerbread\r\nProof of age may be requested at the beginning of the tour for bookings including children.', 'Everyday', 'Weekly Food Tour '),
('', 'What could Paris seriously feel in the 18th century', 'Paris', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d83998.94740156252!2d2.2773451864780037!3d48.858837635028124!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e1f06e2b70f%3A0x40b82c3688c9460!2sParis!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1501590681392" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 200, 2, 'Visites', 'Did you like the novel by Patrick SÃ¼skind? You will love this fragrant and creative ride. The Parisians are said to have a nose. Do as the hero of the book Jean-Baptiste Grenouille and, discover the living and enticing olfactory scenery of the largest reserve of odors in the world: the city of Paris in the 18th century.\r\nThis tour invites you to relive the intrigue of the famous novel in the magic center of the capital. You follow the footsteps of the genius from the popular district of Les Halles in Paris Bourgeois of Saint-Germain-des-PrÃ¨s. Immerse yourself in the fragrance of wig powder, leather coats, tuberose in the entrances cochÃ¨res ... Smell the fetid odors of the cemetery of the Innocents and the hints of the tanneries on the quays of the Seine. Finally, discover the arrogant voluptuousness of rococo perfumes ...', 'Tous les jours', 'What could Paris seriously feel in the 18th century'),
('', 'Wine and Chocolate Pairing', 'Strasbourg ', '', 49, 2, 'French-Gastronomy', 'Description\r\nStrasbourg is the only place where you will meet as passionate a chocolatier as Christophe Meyer, worthy heir of his father Christian, founder of the famous Strasbourg chocolate house.\r\n\r\nChristophe Meyer takes you on a journey through his chocolate made with cocoa selected by Christopher himself and coming from all over world. Along with his exceptional chocolates, let yourself enjoy the sublime wines he  selected specifically for this Wine & Chocolate tasting to find the perfect match.\r\n\r\nThis service is available for groups from 10 persons or more and on request.\r\n\r\nDo not hesitate to contact us to book this unique experience!', 'Everyday on demand for sunday', 'Wine and Chocolate Pairing'),
('', 'Wine tour â€“ The Best of the Bordeaux vineyards by car', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2828.7162533302194!2d-0.5779440850417968!3d44.84771158238791!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527d8f3f36da5%3A0x92522c1fcae6f5cf!2s58+Rue+Ferrere%2C+33000+Bordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499862096534" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 899, 0, 'Wine-Discover', 'Trip Code : Vin 01\r\nTrip activity\r\nSelf-guided wine tour\r\nLocation\r\nBordeaux - France\r\nDuration\r\n7 days\r\nDepartures\r\nEvery day\r\nCapacity\r\nMinimum 2 people\r\nPrice per person\r\n7 days - 6 nights : 899 â‚¬\r\nIncluding services\r\n6 overnights with breakfast in charming guesthouse (in double / twin room)\r\n6 dinners (wine included)\r\n6 wineries visit and wine tasting\r\n1 guided visit of Saint-emilion\r\nRoute notes\r\nEmergency phone call support 7/7\r\nExtra charges\r\n<br>\r\nTour description\r\nEight centuries of history are not enough to explain the huge prestige of the wines of Bordeaux! The amateurs will love this exceptional tour through one of the widest vineyards of the world : Pauillac, Margaux, Haut Medoc, Pomerol, Saint-Emilion, PremiÃ¨res cÃ´tes de Bordeaux, Sauternes, Graves and Pessac LÃ©ognan.\r\n<br>\r\nYou will be welcomed by the producers who will give you all the secrets of their high-class wines, from most industrial ones to the most small-scale ones. You will discover two cooperages, will take part in a tasting initiation, cultural visits and will be accommodated in hotel**, hotel*** or charming guesthouses.\r\n<br>\r\nItinerary:\r\n<br>\r\nDay 1 : Pauillac\r\n\r\nYour stay will begin at the beginning of the afternoon at Pauillac with a the famous ChÃ¢teau Lafite Rotchschild guided tour. This "1st Cru ClassÃ©" Pauillac, with the perfume of almond, violet and bilberry, is worldwide known for its elegance and its delicacy.\r\nSince Louis XV who did it " Wine of the King ", the monarchs pass but the years of the High-class wine of Lafite make the History.\r\nAfter driving in the Medoc, by the wine road, you will join your hotel**, located inside a greenery landscape in the heart of the vineyards. You will have a dinner in an inn located just beside the hotel. The chief will propose to you a traditional meal.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 2 : Haut Medoc and Bordeaux\r\n\r\nIn the morning, you will be awaited just beside your hotel, at ChÃ¢teau d\'Arsac, one of the oldest Fields of the Medoc with its 112 hectares including 40 in Margaux appellation.\r\nThe visit of the wine storehouses and the park with many sculptures, will be followed by a tasting of Cru Bourgeois Haut Medoc and Margaux. 3 bottles of Haut Medoc red wine will be given to you at the time of your departure.\r\nYou will then reach Bordeaux for a free lunch and a free visit of the main districts and monuments of the town of Bordeaux.\r\nDinner in the heart of Bordeaux on the Tourny alleys, in a restaurant with an exceptional wine bar (190 worldwide vintages wines).\r\nNight in hotel*** beside the restaurant, in the heart of historical Bordeaux.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 3 : Pomerol and Saint-Ã©milion\r\n\r\nYou will leave in direction of Libourne for a visit and a tasting in another ChÃ¢teau where one produces Pomerol, described like "a full wine, elegant, equipped with an incomparable bouquet and a smoothness". For many amateurs, subtle and elegant quality is indeed the mark of this wine.\r\nDeparture in direction of St-Emilion and free lunch.\r\nAt the beginning of afternoon, visit of the property of the ChÃ¢teau de MÃ´le, 18th century house where you will spend the night as well. The owners will make you share the charm of this guesthouse and will invite you to discover the perfume of their ground and taste their wine. You will have a dinner in a restaurant of St-Emilion.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 4 : Saint-emilion - oenology and UNESCO patrimony\r\n\r\nThe morning, guided tour (approximately 2 hours) of the underground monuments of the medieval village of St-Emilion, classified within the World Inheritance of Humanity by UNESCO. You will discover the cave of the Monk Emilion, the Vault of the Trinity, the Catacombs, old underground cemetery, and one of the largest monolith church of Europe.\r\nFree lunch in the Medieval City.\r\nAt the beginning of the afternoon, you will be awaited for a tasting initiation with a  professional oenologist. During 1h30, it will present St-Emilion vineyard, various type of vines, before making you recognize the tastes and the flavours of the wines.\r\nYou will then leave Saint-Emilion to Capian and will be received in ChÃ¢teau Grand Branet for the dinner and a night in "Bacchus" 3 ears of corn guesthouse. The owners will be happy to accommodate you in their residence of XVIInd century, in the heart of their wine exploitation.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 5 : PremiÃ¨res cÃ´tes de Bordeaux and Sauternes\r\n\r\nVisit of the property and tasting of PremiÃ¨re cÃ´tes de Bordeaux in company of your hosts.\r\nDeparture for Fargues. Free lunch and visit of the ChÃ¢teau Rieussec. This castle and this vineyard of 110 hectares were acquired by the Baron de Rothschild family in 1984. The liqueur-like wine amateurs will appreciate the wine of Rieussec Castle which is registered since several generations like one of the first references of Sauternes.\r\nDinner in a guesthouse, in the heart of the village of St Symphorien.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 6 : Graves and Pessac Leognan\r\n\r\nAt the end of the morning, you will be awaited by the " impassioned and very interesting " owners of a beautiful chartreuse, located in the middle of a splendid park and vines. They produce Graves wines and will make you visit theirs vines and wine storehouse. You will discover there a small-scale manufacture (the grape is still collected with the hands) and taste white and red wines. You will leave the property with, in remembering, 3 bottles.\r\nFree lunch in a restaurant located beside the property or close to the afternoon visit.\r\nIn the afternoon, visit of the ChÃ¢teau Smith Haut Lafitte, Grand Cru ClassÃ© Graves, Pessac-LÃ©ognan appellation. You will of course taste this well-known wine, after having discovered the underground wine storehouse with wooden barrels, the cooperage of the ChÃ¢teau. You will be able to discover on your own outsides (vines, pond, hotel, restaurant, vinothÃ©rapie center).\r\nNight in a charming guesthouse, in a castle of XVIIIrd century. You will have a dinner in an excellent restaurant with local specialities located at 3 km of the castle.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 7 :\r\n\r\nEnd of this wine tour, the head full of the memory of these sumptuous ChÃ¢teaux and these artists who make them live. Possibility of a free visit of the castle of Montesquieu.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Every day', 'Wine tour â€“ The Best of the Bordeaux vineyards by car'),
('', 'Wine tour â€“ week-end Bordeaux vineyards by car', 'Bordeaux ', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2828.7162533302194!2d-0.5779440850417968!3d44.84771158238791!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527d8f3f36da5%3A0x92522c1fcae6f5cf!2s58+Rue+Ferrere%2C+33000+Bordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499862096534" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 299, 0, 'Wine-Discover', 'Trip Code : Vin 02\r\nTrip activity\r\nSelf-guided wine tour\r\nLocation\r\nBordeaux Saint-emilion Martillac - France\r\nDuration\r\n2 days\r\nDepartures\r\nEvery day\r\nCapacity\r\nMinimum 2 people\r\nPrice per person\r\n2 days - 1 nights : 299 â‚¬\r\nIncluding services\r\n1 overnight with breakfast in charming guesthouse (in double / twin room)\r\n1 dinner and 2 lunches (wine included)\r\n3 winery visits and wine tasting\r\nBottle pack from 2 wineries\r\nRoute notes\r\nEmergency phone call support 7/7\r\nExtra charges\r\nExtra night before or after the journey : 55 to 65 â‚¬\r\n<br>\r\nTour description\r\n<br>\r\nThe amateurs will like this weekend through one of the widest vineyards of the world. You will taste well-known vintage wines like Graves, Pessac LÃ©ognan and Saint-Emilion. You will be welcomed by the producers who will give you all the secrets of their high-class wines, from the most industrial ones to the most small-scale ones. You will taste their production and will set out again with some â€œsamplesâ€. You will be accommodated in a charming guesthouse.\r\n<br>\r\nItinerary:\r\n<br>\r\nDay 1 : Graves and Pessac Leognan\r\n\r\nRendez-vous in country of the Graves vineyards, close to La BrÃ¨de, for a first guided tour, at 10h30 AM.\r\n<br>\r\nThe owners of this beautiful chartreuse, located in the medium of a splendid park and vines, produce Graves wines and will welcome you there for a visit of the vine and wine storehouse.\r\nYou will discover a small-scale manufacture where the grape is still collected with the hand and will taste white and red wines. You will leave the property with 3 bottles.\r\nYou will have a gastronomic lunch in a charming restaurant.\r\n<br>\r\nIn the afternoon, you will be awaited in the ChÃ¢teau Smith Haut Lafitte, for a guided tour of the estate. This one will be completed by a tasting of this wine.\r\nIn 1990, Daniel and Florence, the owners, sell all they have to repurchase Smith Haut Lafitte. After two years of hard work, as well in the farm buildings as in the XVIIIth century chartreuse one, they settle in the castle where they live all of year to devote themself entirely to their new passion: the breeding of the white and red high-class wines of Smith Haut Lafitte.\r\n<br>\r\nThe fermenting being finished, the wine is put in wooden barrels, in the underground wine storehouse which you will discover with your guide. The castle has its own cooperage; it is by this place that you will complete your visit. Rare are the producers manufacturing their own barrels, excepted the most famous ones like Lafitte, PÃ©trus and Margaux.\r\nOnce your visit finished, you may continue to freely visit the outsides of this splendid chartreuse, surrounded of vines, a pond, a hotel and a of vinothÃ©rapie centre attended by many personalities.\r\nAt the end of the afternoon, you will be awaited, few kilometres from there, in another castle, but this time to spend the night there.\r\n<br>\r\nYou will have all the time to install you in this XVIIIth century castle renovated with taste and respect of the stone. The owner will welcome you to make you discover one of the charming rooms.\r\n<br>\r\nYou will have a dinner in an excellent restaurant, in the heart of the vineyard and classified " Gault and Millau ". You will taste regional specialities.\r\n<br>\r\nDay 2 : Saint-Ã©milion\r\n\r\nAfter a good breakfast in the castle, you will leave in direction of one of the many ChÃ¢teaux of Saint-Emilion jurisdiction .\r\n<br>\r\nIn company of your hostess, you will discover the secrets of this prestigious wine, which makes since centuries the fame of Saint-Emilion:\r\n<br>\r\nVisit of the property, wine storehouse...\r\nHistorical and general presentation of Saint-Emilion name, classification of the vintages.\r\nEvocation of the topography of the vineyard, the nature of the grounds, type of vines, the vegetative cycle and the work of the vine\r\nInitiation to the wine making and the breeding of the wine\r\nTasting of few wines.\r\n<br>\r\nYou will set out again with a 2 bottles of the production.\r\n<br>\r\nHowever, the great value of the wines of Saint-Emilion is not only gustatory, it is also an emotional value, aesthetic, and a placement appreciated by collectors of the whole world.\r\nYou will have a lunch in an excellent restaurant located in the heart of the medieval village of Saint-Emilion.\r\n<br>\r\nDuring the afternoon, free visits of the medieval city of Saint-Emilion, classified within the World Inheritance of Humanity by UNESCO. Saint-Emilion comes from the name of the monk who settled in a cave, as a hermit, at the 8th century. The village, surrounded by famous and prestigious vineyards, is one of the richest in historic buildings. One finds there in particular, a monolith church, built from the 9th century to the 12th century, the largest of Europe.\r\n<br>\r\nEnd of this wine tour, the head full of the memory of these sumptuous residences and these artists who make them live.', 'Everyday', 'Wine tour â€“ week-end Bordeaux vineyards â€¦ by car'),
('', 'Wine tour â€“ Wine road from the Medoc to Saint-emilion by c', 'Bordeaux', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2828.7162533302194!2d-0.5779440850417968!3d44.84771158238791!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5527d8f3f36da5%3A0x92522c1fcae6f5cf!2s58+Rue+Ferrere%2C+33000+Bordeaux!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499862096534" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 419, 0, 'Wine-Discover ', 'Trip Code : Vin 04\r\nTrip activity\r\nSelf-guided wine tour\r\nLocation\r\nBordeaux Pauillac Saint-emilion - France\r\nDuration\r\n4 days\r\nDepartures\r\nEvery day\r\nCapacity\r\nMinimum 2 people\r\nPrice per person\r\n4 days - 3 nights : 419 â‚¬\r\nIncluding services\r\n3 overnights with breakfast in charming guesthouse (in double / twin room)\r\n3 dinners (wine included)\r\n3 wineries visit and wine tasting\r\nRoute notes\r\nEmergency phone call support 7/7\r\n<br>\r\nTour description\r\nLiving in freedom on the road of wines of the MÃ©doc and Saint-Emilion court. Program, nights in the homes of charm in the heart of the vineyards, visiting wineries and tasting great wines, tasting initiation. Grand Cru Pauillac Cru Bourgeois Moulis and Saint-Emilion Grand Cru. Come you initiate or deepen your knowledge of the terroirs in Bordeaux staying there some time!\r\n\r\n<br>\r\nItinerary:\r\n<br>\r\nDay 1 and 2: MÃ©doc\r\n\r\nVisit the land of the Medoc wine peninsula between the Gironde estuary and coastal ocean .\r\nYou will be greeted in a beautiful area in the heart of the vineyards of Medoc red . You will be hosted in room and breakfast in a comfortable , abundant environmental quality benefits: spacious rooms , saltwater pool , table d\'hÃ´te combining tradition and contemporary cuisine. Depending on the season , theme nights are organized poolside pool house or terrace ( Spanish plancha grill ) .\r\nTable d\'hote , bed and breakfast .\r\nThe next day, you\'ll stay in two wine property , one in morning and one in the afternoon : a Cru Bourgeois Moulis and Grand Cru ClassÃ© Pauillac.\r\nProgram , visits to caves and cellars , wine tasting production , visit the Museum ( in the old cellars of the castle) and projection of film about Art and Crafts of Vine and Wine :\r\nThis permanent exhibition offers visitors a complete inventory of the vine to the wine tasting , through the work of the vineyard, cellar and wine tasting . It does not fail to present Annexes trades directly related to the life of the wine , such as the manufacture of barrels (full Cooperage ) , plugs , glass tasting , as well as a vinous imaging, which extends the label engravings and many others sometimes unusual objects. Back to domain for your second night ( table d\'hÃ´te )\r\n<br>\r\nDay 3 and 4: Jurisdiction of Saint -Emilion\r\n\r\nAfter a good breakfast in the area , you will go to the medieval town of Saint -Emilion and its prestigious vineyards , both World Heritage of UNESCO.\r\nTake time to stroll through the streets of the city and stop at one of the many restaurants .\r\nIn the afternoon , visit a castle producer jurisdiction of Saint -Emilion Grand Cru organic wine developed through the guidance and expertise of StÃ©phane Derenoncourt\r\nVisit property, chests , chai ...\r\nHistorical presentation of the property and the general Saint-Emilion , ranked wines.\r\nEvocation of the topography of the vineyard , nature of soil, grape varieties , the vegetative cycle and work in the vineyard\r\nIntroduction to vinification and aging wine\r\nTasting of several vintages .\r\nIn the late afternoon , welcome to the Castle Mole , 18th century where you will also stay overnight . Owners will share the charm of this guest house , located in the castle and invite you to discover the allure of their land and enjoy their wine.\r\nDinner at a restaurant in St Emilion .\r\nTo conclude your stay, the last day , you will be greeted by late morning in Saint -Emilion for an introductory course in oenology and tasting led by a professional oenologist\r\nEnd of the journey on the road of wines from our beautiful region , head full of memories of these magnificent residences and artists who support them.', 'Everyday', 'Wine tour â€“ Wine road from the Medoc to Saint-emilion by c');
