INSERT INTO `blog` (`slug`, `titre`, `description`, `auteur`, `datecrea`, `dateupdate`) VALUES
('Normandy-and-Brittany', 'Normandy and Brittany', 'August is the most touristic season in France, so we advise you to avoid Paris and the French Riviera, where the heat can be difficult to bear.\r\n\r\nTo escape the crowd and the overwhelming heat, Escapade FranÃ§aise offers you the opportunity to recharge your batteries in Normandy and Brittany, two of the most exceptional regions in France with resplendent landscapes this time of year, both on sea and inland.\r\n\r\nThere are many activities and monuments to admire, as well as many festivals. You can enjoy the â€œMusicales de Normandieâ€, a mix of world music, French traditional music and classical music. From the recital to the orchestra, the festival focuses on internationally renowned artists as well as promising young talents.\r\n\r\nIf you stay until the beginning of September, do not miss the American Film Festival in Deauville, where you will have the chance to encounter many celebrities, from France and even Hollywood depending on the program. In Brittany, Celtic music is often honored, with festivities such as village balls where you can learn traditional dances. Throughout the entire summer, the Arts Festival, at the tip of Finistere, brings together more than 30,000 people and combines religious and contemporary art in a very unique way.\r\n\r\nOur Weather Book\r\nWhether it is in Brittany or in Normandy, one can never escape the rain. But do not worry, without rain, the charm of the region wonâ€™t be the same! It is part of the experience, even if the summer tends to have less rain than usual.\r\n\r\nYou will still have plenty of sun, with estimated temperatures between 18 Â° C and 25 Â° C during daytime. For those wanting to go for a dip, the average temperature of the water is 18 Â° C in Deauville and Honfleur, while it is cooler in Etretat and Cherbourg (17.6 Â° C and 17.3 Â° C respectively). ', 'Heloise Melen', '2017-08-18 09:02:33', '2017-08-18 09:04:16'),
('The-French-Riviera', 'The French Riviera', 'In September, favor the French Riviera.\r\nWith the school year vacation coming to an end, the month of September is the perfect time to go discover the French Riviera within all its authenticity. The beaches are empty, and the region transforms itself into a little piece of heaven. Communicating with locals will be much simpler, and they will be able to initiate you to their charming accent. Strolling through the markets and savor the local specialties in charming restaurants will turn into a daily pleasure. In addition to all the activities that we offer throughout the whole year, Escapade FranÃ§aise offers a selection of events and outings not to be missed.\r\nThe region is a little gem for outdoors music festivals: until the end of September, you will have the opportunity to listen to high quality jazz at the Cagnes-sur-Mer festival, every Friday in the castle square, it is ultimately an idyllic environment. In Saint RaphaÃ«l between the 15th and the 17th of September, the inevitable festival of string quartels occurs with quality animations that will make your trip extra than just the Mediterranean coast.\r\nIn Cannes, the yachting festival welcomes numerous international exhibitors that will introduce you to the nautical pleasures; you would be able to admire the latestâ€™s boats of the biggest shipyards in the world. Cannes remains faithful to its reputation as the leading fair in the world. For the gourmets, the national festival of gastronomy happens from the 22nd to the 24th of September. Amateurs and notorious specialists of culinary food meet around delicious cooked meals and tastings of local products to have the chance to share unusual flavors. Those flavors are French and exclusively from the southern region.\r\n\r\nOur weather book note:\r\n\r\nIn the French Riviera, the nice weather and the summer temperatures are on point in September. It is estimated the weather will be between 22Â°C and 27Â°C during the day, and drop a few degrees in the evening. The rain is rare, yet there is often mistral, wind, however personalize the Provence climate originality. You can also bathe with serenity in the Mediterranean Sea: the seasonal averages are between 20,3Â°C and 22,5Â°C.', 'Heloise Melen', '2017-08-18 09:07:56', '2017-08-18 09:07:56');
