('', '', 'Le Petit Jardin', 'Marseille', 10, 'Le Petit Jardin is a bed and breakfast with two rooms in a very good location within the heart of the 7th district (itself in the center of the city). The 7th district is one of the most beautiful and typical places in Marseille. Close to the Propheteâ€™s beach, close to Notre Dame de La Garde and close to the Vieux Port, our bed and breakfast is easily linked to all the majors places to be visited by public transports and self service bike system.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2904.6804245424514!2d5.360237514899297!3d43.27907048456132!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12c9c72d7e656867%3A0x31bd1cc9e4ad1c3f!2s136+Chemin+du+Vallon+de+l&#39;Oriol%2C+13007+Marseille!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499863821598" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('', '', 'Les Aurochs', 'French Riviera', 15, 'At the heart of the Gulf of Saint- Tropez, this old sheepfold, out of sight and near the castle of grimaud, will seduce you with its tranquility.\r\n\r\nThe guesthouse "The Aurochs " offers a real moment of authenticity, simplicity and sweetness.\r\n\r\nLean back, the atmosphere and the welcoming hosts will make the rest !\r\n\r\nHere, we enjoy life, we have a laugh around the swimming pool, we share a glass of rosÃ©, a cocktail dinner, for a weekend or a week, with friends or family, you will feel delighted.\r\n\r\nYour only regret : that you eventually have to leave us.\r\n\r\nOur five Holiday cottages and our 2 guest rooms with a refined decoration, have air conditioning for hot summer nights, a mini bar for a drink or to celebrate a magical moment.\r\n\r\nIn the shade of palm trees, sun lovers can safely relax around the swimming pool.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2904.3160329048637!2d6.518357315553424!3d43.286702979135605!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12cec9c48f9488af%3A0x3c1ec5ca6759e972!2sLES+AUROCHS!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490349608513" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide204" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="G7rSxA24" class="TA_links DmSw6Ecv4So">\r\n<li id="SWMmjOX" class="AYF2uZeI">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=204&amp;locationId=4607584&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Les Bruyeres du Mont Saint-Michel', 'Normandie/ Bretagne', 30, 'The Guest house is in the bay of Mont Saint Michel\r\nLocated between Avranches and Mont St Michel, the guest house "Les BruyÃ¨res du Mont" is an old farmhouse with a large flower garden.\r\n \r\nThe House has a Southern exposure and is sheltered from the winds, the location is also very peaceful.\r\n\r\nFun, sporting and family activities are available at the guest house.\r\nBicycle hire, board games, French bowls or table tennis are available on site.\r\n\r\nThe garden of the guest house, is sunny with terraced areas that are in the shade of the tall trees.\r\n\r\n\r\nLes BruyÃ¨res du Mont, is amongst the heather and has astonishing luxury vegetation because we are passionate about our garden. Depending on the season, we use our fruit and vegetables from our garden in our jams or compotes and in our meals.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1704979.1550291476!2d-2.868907643430964!3d48.51305860936419!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480954acdede638b%3A0xc9cfe1bbc1613bf!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+Les+Bruy%C3%A8res+du+Mont!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490281615592"  frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide943" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="kPPF4F" class="TA_links 3IGt0FdtlT5a">\r\n<li id="XcsxcM" class="QXsv9GU3T">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=943&amp;locationId=7395384&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Les Chambres de l Abbaye', 'Marseille', 10, 'Welcome at Les Chambres de l\'Abbaye.<br>\r\nIn the bend of a peacefull alley, in the center of Marseille these restaured workshop turned into a guesthouse, proposes you a quiet housing with parking.<br>\r\nLocated at only one minute to the Old Port and a 10min walk to the Pharo (the), the 3 rooms of the lovely geusthouse -Les Chambres de l\'Abbaye- welcomes you all year long in Marseille. \r\nTwo of the three rooms can welcome 3 people, and the breakfast is served in the garden by the hostress, Arlette, and in the dining room during winter, next to a fire in the chimney. <br>\r\nYou will be proposed jams and cakes but also viennoiseries and fresh fruitjuice every morning.\r\nThe common transports can be joined by foot.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2904.084504486895!2d5.366088315553597!3d43.29155197913539!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12c9c0c60d5df6bf%3A0x36bc1728cb7e47d6!2sLes+Chambres+de+l%E2%80%99Abbaye!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1493134274142" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('', '', 'Les Hauts d Etretat', 'Normandie/ Bretagne', 10, 'Les Hauts dâ€™Etretat is a lovely normand house located a stone\'s throw away from the famous city of Etretat. Its legendary cliffs and pebbles beaches, place of inspiration of various artists, will dive you into a wonderful change of scenery. <br>\r\nBucolic space in a lovely house, mixing top of the range performances and authenticity in an absolut calm, our cottage with its lovely garden and peaceful rooms will bring you a unique atmosphere and way of living on the albaster coast.<br>\r\nIn spring in the park with birds singing or in winter while it turns under the snow into a fairy house, you will be conquered by Les Hauts dâ€™Etretat.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2581.3197071502564!2d0.23465531576388243!3d49.68595197937722!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e03d89559fda3f%3A0x8de10d42cdec4ed5!2sLes+Hauts+d&#39;Etretat!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1493138955553" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide919" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="dRTfRbqWZ" class="TA_links mzE8JsHi">\r\n<li id="cjM2RcLxI" class="k9WRB5A5T4t">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=919&amp;locationId=10430248&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Les Rosees', 'French Riviera', 10, 'Welcome to Les Rosees, an inviting guest house located opposite the picturesque medieval village of Mougins. Soothingly simple yet refined, this authentic Provencal Mas is a perfect haven for both romantic and family retreats. The 400 year old bastide has been lovingly renovated using only ancient restoration techniques. A mix of beautiful antique furniture and contemporary luxury provide guests with an authentic Provencal experience in endulging comfort. At Les Rosees we pride ourselves with regional and traditional Provencal dishes sourced in the mornings at the surrounding village markets. Come take a rest by the swimming pool while we prepare your meals, read a book under the olive tree, enjoy a siesta on a lounge chair or wander through our Mediterranean rose garden. Take time and replenish yourself!\r\n', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2888.9370603344455!2d6.990661915563423!3d43.60785207912274!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12cc2985816e05dd%3A0xa66d544ef8ac9a4d!2sLes+Ros%C3%A9es!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1492597916583" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide819" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="VQh5gty" class="TA_links UK9E6AYf">\r\n<li id="QlGEU2" class="fIkrTgG1jV">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=819&amp;locationId=603968&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Manoir de la Baronnie', 'Normandie/ Bretagne', 12, 'Come and enjoy the breathtaking city of Saint Malo !\r\nFor an unforgettable stay, discover an authentic Manor owned and runned by a family.\r\n\r\nLocated in the heart of Saint-Malo, next to several beaches and to the historical centre but away from touristic crowds, you will be seduced by this original 18th century Manor.\r\nBedrooms are all unique and typically furnished with antique furniture from the region.\r\n\r\nBreakfast are made of local products and could be served either in the "Grand Salon" or in the garden.\r\nBenoÃ®t and Sophie LAUDE, the owners, are at your entire disposal should you need any advise about worthseeing places or "must do".\r\n\r\nYou wish to rest and relax ? Enjoy the private spa !\r\nLooking for something more exotic ? You should sleep in the traditional gipsy caravan located in the park...\r\nLooking forward to seeing you soon at La Baronnie !', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2637.316659838817!2d-1.9992817842726076!3d48.62292217926509!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x480e8154c427267b%3A0xa71c62b9c9b1edc8!2sManoir+de+la+Baronnie!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488376627310" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide628" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="7aujW0ON" class="TA_links 3tG7nPettO">\r\n<li id="9ncZhEfJG7r" class="zw06m5">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=628&amp;locationId=2018543&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'My Home For You', 'Paris', 20, 'Wishing to experience Paris differently ?\r\nChoose an urban guest-house in which everything is gathered so that you feel at home. Your host, Jean Ã‰tienne, welcomes you warmly! His professional experience in the Parisian tourism and luxury hotel business prompted him to imagine this new place. Today, he invites you to discover an ideal address to live and discover Paris differently: My Home For You.\r\nMy Home For You is situated in a beautiful building dating from 1875. Located on number 10, Boulevard PoissonniÃ¨re, in the 9th district, we are right in the heart of Paris, in front of the renowned cinema Le Grand Rex.\r\nThe apartment has been completely renovated in 2015. We paid particular attention to the comfort and decoration of every part of the apartment, of every room. Furnished with family furniture, along with pieces found in the Parisian auction house â€˜Drouotâ€™ or in antique dealers, the apartment boasts paintings and engravings from the 19th century, as well as authentic reproductions of designer icons (Le Corbusierâ€™s deckchair â€˜LC4â€™ or Mies van der Roheâ€™s armchair â€˜Barcelonaâ€™ to name a few). Each bedroom plunges you into a unique atmosphere, taking inspiration from the diverse Parisian districts (Palais Royal, Grand boulevards, TrocadÃ©ro) or even from the National Museum of the Asiatic Arts - Guimet.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2624.3245265696114!2d2.3447570157358455!3d48.87108967928882!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66e160b05be8b%3A0x4e2438c944ed6dd1!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes-B%26B+Paris+%22My+Home+For+You%22!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490195685904" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide54" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="R3E5yO8ukcOL" class="TA_links q4ZOOc1Yo8IE">\r\n<li id="JUFjpt8L1UQ1" class="008nVJ5">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=54&amp;locationId=10062820&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>\r\n'),
('', '', 'Villa Arguibel', 'Biarritz', 15, 'Arguibel, at Guethary, near Biarritz, is a place that mixes luxury and design in a concept that stands between the hostel and the top of the range guesthouse. There is an amazing view on the ocean and the Pays Basqueâ€™s montains.<br>\r\nThe villa has 5 rooms including 2 suites to offer, with an original decoration that mixes ancient furnitures and contemporary paintings. You will love the terrace to enjoy your delicious breakfasts and rest in a wonderful and calm dÃ©cor.<br>\r\nArguibelâ€™s living room will welcome you chatting time with friends or resting time. You will enjoy its private bar and library. The villa, between Biarritz and St Jean de Luz, is located a km away from the ocean and the beaches. <br>\r\n', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3101923.2999439165!2d-4.832418311786236!3d42.47058806677543!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd5113f56719a647%3A0x64b72f698b758721!2sArguibel!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1490283579721" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide381" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="4YmE7gCBd" class="TA_links OgPA3HvCi2Sw">\r\n<li id="IYCsb13R" class="ySnWJzZmF">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=381&amp;locationId=1566677&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Villa du Square', 'Paris', 25, 'Located in Parisâ€™s much coveted 16th arrondissement and nestling between the Seine river and the Bois de Boulogne, the Villa du Square is truly a hidden gem. This intimate Bed and Breakfast set in a leafy private alley offers you an exclusive and original stay in Paris.\r\nThe house has a long standing history and is not a newly created guest house with artificial charm nor a soulless designer hotel. Tastefully decorated in an eclectic style, the Villa du Square provides an  unique opportunity to enjoy the French way of life in an exquisite Parisian setting.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2625.3336109401093!2d2.262618215735212!3d48.85184847928693!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e67ab1e5b6862f%3A0xc893dea8d083c8a5!2sVilla+Du+Square!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279376977" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide812" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="bg0WOM2eE" class="TA_links Cwu7HoLb3">\r\n<li id="R5VBJ2yL2t" class="bOMQe4Yl">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=812&amp;locationId=8117151&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Villa Goeland', 'Biarritz', 15, 'Elisabeth and Paul would be delighted to welcome you at the â€œVilla le Goelandâ€œ.\r\nThis beautiful manor with its traditional architecture has been in our family for generations,\r\nExtremely well placed in the town and only 50 meters from one of the most beautiful beaches in Biarritz.\r\nYou can experience a 180Â° panoramic view from Spain in the south to the French coast in the North from the comfort of the villas large rooms. With the building being centrally located, you can take advantage of all the shopping, sportingand cultural activities offered in the town. Being a family home, we have no main dining facilities, however we can direct you to the vast array of nearby restaurants, offering both fine dining and local cuisine. Constructed in the 18th Century, the Villa was first known as the Villa Ravize and subsequently was called the Villa Montebello, until it underwent its last extensive architectural modification in 1900 and 1903 whereafter it was transformed into the â€œVilla le Goelandâ€œ.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2894.945383051869!2d-1.5684959844404742!3d43.482610179127505!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0xd516b257f8300ad%3A0x9663e1cac8c29ec6!2sVilla+le+Go%C3%A9land!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488279454147" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide842" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="AgCqN3eZB" class="TA_links xGFDK7Vewl0">\r\n<li id="z8cLBcnO6qs" class="I4hbno5dmeCi">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=842&amp;locationId=312448&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Villa Montabord', 'Paris', 100, 'Isabelle and Jeromeâ€™s house is the second of two mansions built in 1860 by one of the â€œCitÃ© des Fleursâ€ founders for each of his daughters.\r\n\r\nOnce through the gates, you enter a small enclosed garden in the front of a beautiful stone facade, with a charming wooden terrace, topped by a young fig tree and garnished with plants and flowers as soon as the weather is nice. Climb up the steps and you are in one of the very rare guest houses in Paris.\r\n\r\nIn the large hall paved with black and white tiles and lit with a Murano red glass chandelier, you will be welcomed personally and will start feeling the intimate and authentic atmosphere that makes the real charm of homestays.\r\n\r\nA splendid staircase covered with soft carpet leads up to both floors reserved for guests, each with two large bedrooms named after their children, with dressing room, private bathrooms and separate toilets.\r\n\r\nIn the mornings, breakfast is served in the private dining room on the ground floor. Basking in the light from both the living room and inner courtyard, and under the mischievous look of a girl in a graceful pose (terracotta bust by Belgian sculptor Georges Van der Straeten), you will enjoy a delicious and lavish homemade breakfast while planning the day with Isabelle and Jeromeâ€™s helpful advice.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2623.250186216353!2d2.317217315736535!3d48.89156897929075!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47e66fac024ea99d%3A0xcb690ad92df0a041!2sChambres+d&#39;h%C3%B4tes+B%26B+Paris+Villa+Montabord!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1488278513586" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide821" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="bhqgOU92T04a" class="TA_links C2rL4J">\r\n<li id="7OzDNl6On" class="4vnJiXIimtjd">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.fr/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.fr/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=821&amp;locationId=7906143&amp;lang=eng_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>'),
('', '', 'Villa Monticelli', 'Marseille', 10, 'Welcome to the Monticelli Villa. 15 minutes away from the historical city heart of Marseille and Vieux Port, both Colette and Jean Paranque welcome you to their Tuscany inspired Villa and offer you their stylish rooms.\r\n\r\nA gourmet breakfast will be served including a wide range of homemade jams on a picturesque terrace. Several restaurants are located about 5 minutes by foot from the Monticelli Villa.\r\n\r\nOur charming guesthouse is located right in the centre of the 8th district of Marseille, probably the most beautiful suburb of the town. The welcome lives up to our homely atmosphere.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2905.047113566912!2d5.380429515552947!3d43.27138877913624!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12c9c74fef109349%3A0x33110cb280d21c81!2sVilla+Monticelli!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1493133710303" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('', '', 'Villa Stella', 'Paris', 0, 'The Stella Cadente Guests House in Provins offers you 4 guests bedrooms with charm and a family suite (2 bedrooms-1 living room).\r\n\r\nIts fairy tale atmosphÃ¨re, its original and sophisticated decoration offer an absolute change of scenery for a romantic weekend, a family holiday, an escapade with friends, or also for a pleasant alternative to hÃ´tel as a professional stopping place.  \r\n\r\nWhether you appropriate one of our guests bedrooms, our family suite or you privatize the whole House for a spÃ©cial occasion (bachelorette parties, weddings, birthdays, family gatherings, mini seminarsâ€¦) you will be delighted.\r\n\r\nWe welcome you as Stella Cadenteâ€™s friends, show you around the house so that you feel at once Â« at home Â», and make every effort for you to spend the visit you dreamt of.\r\n\r\nLocated at the crossroads of Champagne, Bourgogne and Ile de France, our Guests House is an ideal stopover near Paris on the North-South and East-West axes. It is also the ideal place for a several days stay.\r\n\r\nReferenced with the Gites de France, our Guests bedrooms are qualified Â« 4-Ã©pis Â». We are also recommended by the Figaro Magazine, the Petit FutÃ©, The Ile de France Guide Vert Michelin , booking.com , TripAdvisorâ€¦\r\n\r\nAt the heart of medieval city of Provins, our House rises at the Cesar Tower.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2640.6260864081924!2d3.2884603151048917!3d48.5595563296559!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x47ef31a8e043eb6b%3A0x72aba86783e3d095!2s28+Rue+Maximilien+Michelin%2C+77160+Provins!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1499863492171" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', ''),
('', '', 'Villa Stephanie', 'French Riviera', 10, 'StÃ©phanie and Olivier welcome you in their charming guest house located at the gates of Cannes,\r\nIn the heart of the CÃ´te d\'Azur, enjoying a view of the Mediterranean Sea, from the LÃ©rins Islands to the Esterel.\r\nThe Villa StÃ©phanie is ideally located, in the town of Mougins overlooking the city of Cannes, only 10 minutes from the Croisette and its beaches.\r\nFrom the house easy and fast access, you can reach all the tourist destinations of the Provence Alpes CÃ´tes D\'Azur region.\r\nThis charming guest house has two double sea view rooms with terraces, and three suites with terraces, a heated pool all year round and covered from October to May for your comfort in all seasons.', '<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2889.9780765974565!2d7.008912315562747!3d43.586172979123596!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x12cc2a1cb735f847%3A0xc2ed6fe7e54e2425!2sVilla+Stephanie+Maison+d&#39;hotes!5e0!3m2!1sfr!2sfr!4v1492604909671" frameborder="0" style="" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<div id="TA_cdsratingsonlywide785" class="TA_cdsratingsonlywide">\r\n<ul id="rDlru2k5" class="TA_links hPfKtvZk8ONT">\r\n<li id="kahTNB1" class="lNpNftqJZ">\r\n<a target="_blank" href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/"><img src="https://www.tripadvisor.com/img/cdsi/img2/branding/tripadvisor_logo_transp_340x80-18034-2.png" alt="TripAdvisor"/></a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<script src="https://www.jscache.com/wejs?wtype=cdsratingsonlywide&amp;uniq=785&amp;locationId=3399848&amp;lang=en_US&amp;border=true&amp;shadow=true&amp;display_version=2"></script>');
