INSERT INTO `ville` (`ville`, `genre`, `description_ville`, `id`) VALUES
('Biarritz', 'SEA', 'By the shore, Biarritz is wideword known for the thalassothÃ©rapie, born in the 1970\'. <br>\r\nWith its various activities, Biarritz est the perfect place for family holidays , and to enjoy nautical activities : surf, walks on the beach with an amazing light,...<br>\r\nFor the sporty ones, Biarritz in even known as the european sport capital. It also rimes with golf : the golf lovers will have plenty of choice among the 10 that exist in a beam of 50km.\r\nAn authentic town that will entertain you, from the young ones to the oldest.', 'Biarritz'),
('Normandie/ Bretagne', 'SEA', 'Britanny and Normandy are two areas linked by their rich history. They will bring you an essential break among nature, breathtaking marine and terrestrial landscapes. Come and discover the Mont-Saint-Michel, the Etretat cliffs or the D-Day beaches in Normandy, and enjoy the Saint-Maloâ€™s bastions or the path of the Douaniers at the very edge of Britanny, at the Pointe Saint-Mathieu. Eventually, do not forget to taste the local food products that will excite all your senses.', 'Normandie'),
('Bordeaux', 'CITY', 'Come and visit the "CitÃ© du vin", capital of the greatest wine-growing place in France, having with an international reputation thanks to its protected designation of origin.<br>\r\nHave a stay in a cosmopolitan city where wine and gastronomy goes together. As an identity, you will find everywhere on Bordeaux prints of the role of the wine in its activity.<br>\r\nYou can be a lover of fine wine such as Sauternes, Saint-Emilion or Chateau Margaux, or you can wish awake your senses, our guesthouses in Bordeaux will permit you to  enjoy a unique bucolic frame around the vineyards.', 'Bordeaux'),
('Strasbourg', 'CITY', 'Located in the east of France, Strasbourg counts among the UNESCO worlwide patrimoine, for the wealth of its architecture and beauty.<br>\r\nIt is considered in France a the christmas capital, due to its exceptionnal christmas market, known for almost 450 years.<br/>\r\nWith New-York and Geneva, Strasbourg is one of the only city that welcomes international institutions without being capital of State.<br>\r\nYou will discover a rich gastronomy, come and taste the choucroute or the famous foie gras in friendly taverns. You should aslo try the alsacienne beer, its invention dates back to 1268!\r\n oÃ¹ vous dÃ©couvrirez la biÃ¨re.<br>\r\nYou can like castles, prefer bikes, want to try good restaurants, you will be able to do everything ! <br>\r\nStrasbourg deserves your curiosity.', 'Strasbourg'),
('Paris', 'CITY', 'French capital, Paris is not only known for being the most beautiful city in the world. Paris, this is a harmonious mix between art, fashion, literature, gastronomy,...<br>\r\nThe exceptional culture have an exciting story, the architecture composed of great buildings such as the Eiffel Tower, or the Notre-Dame cathedral is impressive.<br>\r\nWandering around in the small streets, taste a french baguette and a croissant at breakfast, admire the beauty of the monuments, discover a new way of thinking and meet parisians will make your getaway unforgettable.<br>\r\nParis will give you its positiv energy at every moment.', 'Paris'),
('Haute-Savoie', 'MOUNTAIN', 'The Haute-Savoie welcomes you by summer and winter with its lakes (Annecy, LÃ©man, its montains such as the Mont)Blanc, its ski stations and international meetings all year long.\r\nYou can be here for holidays or for professional reasons, you will find in our guide all the usefull informations about Haute-Savoie : housing, entertainment, events, monuments and natural or historical curiosities. You will also find shops, services and good restaurants. ', 'Haute-Savoie'),
('French Riviera', 'SEA', 'In 1923, two young amercian, Gerald and Sara Murphy discovered the beauty of the city of Antibes, so far unknown. They convinced their Hotel du Cap boss to open in summer, while the main part of famous people came during winter.<br> Murphy invited lots of friends and notables such as Pablo Picasso or Ernest Hemingway who made this area appreciated. <br />\r\nThis is how the name "French Riviera" (or "CÃ´te d\'Azur in french, for the colour of the sea) was born. This appellation includes the eastern part of the coast, includind Monaco.<br>\r\nDuring your stay, you will discover breathtaking landscapes and famous cities such as Saint-Tropez, Cannes, Nice,...', 'French-Riviera'),
('PolynÃ©sie FranÃ§aise', 'SEA', 'Situated in the heart of the Pacific Ocean, the French Polynesia is a maritime space of 4millions of km2, just like Europe.<br>\r\nThe Frenhc Polynesia inspired generations of explorers, authors, painters, travellers,...<br>\r\nThe big island rises majestically on the top of the lagoons of opal.<br>\r\nBetween the parties and festivals, the mythology and beliefs, the archeological and historical discovers (danse, tatoos), there is always something inspiring for each and every one of us.<br>\r\nDiscover the local specialties, have fun on traditionnal rythms on the beach with amazing dancers. Let yourself go among these beautiful places and famous island like ThaÃ¯ti, Bora Bora and much more.\r\nthe French Polynesia is definitely waiting for you!', 'Frenchpolynesia'),
('Corse', 'SEA', 'Commonly called Â« beauty island Â» for her natural unique patrimony and her sunny weather. Heavenly looking beaches at the interior of most hidden villages. Corse is a beautiful island with many secrets and savage force. Itâ€™s an island with astonish places in summer, enjoy the walk and many nautical activities and during the long winter soak in the deep Corse, discover the making of local products and appreciate the Corse wine while learning the language spoken there, Italian. Corse will seduce you for a memorable escapade.', 'Corse'),
('Marseille', 'SEA', 'Marseille, also known as "the gate to the world", is the oldest city in France â€“ built around its important commercial port. Founded in 600 BC by Greek sailors of Phocaea, Marseille is the first port of France. It is also the main quarters of an archbishop, the city of university and the capital of the departments Bouches-du-Rhone. The city owes its expansion and prosperity to its port, which is an important trans-shipment point with goods destined for North Africa and Asia, especially the petol that occupies an eminent position.\n', 'Marseille'),
('Reims', 'COUNTRYSIDE', 'Reims has a story that dates back to the oldest times. You can\'t imagine what waits for you there!<br>\r\nFrom the gallo-romaine time to nowadays, Reims played a major role in history.\r\nReims, romain capital, city where the kings were coronated, martyred city during the First World War, architectural laboratory, symbol of peace and reconciliation... <br>\r\nMany expressions to nominate a multifaceted city, capital of the North, seat of Clovis\'s batism, bombarded and almost entirely destroyed during the Second world war, rebuild in the 1920\' and 1930\' in an art deco style. It was also Eisenhower\'s general headquarters, where Germany signed its capitulation the 7th of may 1945. <br>\r\nThe 3 sites ranked in the Unesco world heritage, the amazing monuments and museums testify of this historic past.', 'Reims');
